WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.317 --> 00:00:04.687
MATT: Hello, everyone! And welcome to tonight's
episode of Critical Role One-Shots, where we have

00:00:04.687 --> 00:00:10.132
taken over the slot of "No Survivors" this Monday
thanks to the illustrious generosity of the

00:00:10.132 --> 00:00:12.026
fantastic Ivan Van Norman.

00:00:12.026 --> 00:00:17.219
IVAN: Any day, you may take the slot whenever you
wish, especially when I get to be a player.

00:00:17.219 --> 00:00:22.470
MATT: I like it when Ivan tells me it's okay for
me to "take his slot." The way he says it. But

00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:29.044
yeah, so this evening we have the fantastic
pleasure of running a one-shot game of Pathfinder,

00:00:29.044 --> 00:00:33.072
which, for those of you who haven't played,
Pathfinder is a fantastic fantasy RPG, it's

00:00:33.072 --> 00:00:38.478
actually what we played for the first two years of
Critical Role. And tonight we get to show a fun

00:00:38.478 --> 00:00:44.496
story that we've put together for this series of
players here, as well as show off the really cool

00:00:44.496 --> 00:00:48.330
software Syrinscape, which I mentioned a few times
in the show, I use it to organize a lot of the

00:00:48.330 --> 00:00:53.410
music and sound cues for Critical Role, we get to
show you some more of what it's capable of tonight

00:00:53.410 --> 00:00:57.650
outside of my custom settings, this is what the
actual setup itself can do, which is phenomenal.

00:00:57.650 --> 00:01:03.001
So, super excited to back that. Before we get
started, let me go ahead and introduce our

00:01:03.001 --> 00:01:08.613
fantastic players for this evening. We have on the
table to my left, we have Ivan, who you've already

00:01:08.613 --> 00:01:12.633
seen thus far, Ivan Van Norman, hello. Thank you
for joining us.

00:01:12.633 --> 00:01:15.384
IVAN: I am happy to be here. Thank you for having
me.

00:01:15.384 --> 00:01:18.398
MATT: Yay! We have Marisha Ray from Critical
Role.

00:01:18.398 --> 00:01:19.818
MARISHA: Hi, guys!

00:01:19.818 --> 00:01:24.159
MATT: And to the other table, we have Taliesin
Jaffe from Critical Role.

00:01:24.159 --> 00:01:25.390
TALIESIN: Hi!

00:01:25.390 --> 00:01:29.752
MATT: And our very two special guests joining us
this evening, Ashly Burch--

00:01:29.752 --> 00:01:30.828
ASHLY: Hello!

00:01:30.828 --> 00:01:33.328
MATT: And Phil Lamarr!

00:01:33.328 --> 00:01:42.625
PHIL: (deep voice) Why, hi there! I'm going to use
this voice all night! For no good reason. A goblin

00:01:42.625 --> 00:01:44.295
with a large set of testicles.

00:01:44.295 --> 00:01:45.909
(laughter)

00:01:45.909 --> 00:01:48.742
MATT: Which, to let you guys know, tonight's game
is going to be interesting because unlike a lot of

00:01:48.742 --> 00:01:54.804
other fantasy RPGs, tonight the whole party is
goblins. Everyone are playing goblins, we'll go

00:01:54.804 --> 00:01:59.572
ahead and do some quick introductions as to who
you're playing, starting clockwise back from how

00:01:59.572 --> 00:02:01.867
we were introduced. So, Phil, who are you playing
as?

00:02:01.867 --> 00:02:14.371
PHIL: I'm playing as Browntooth the rogue. Goblin
rogue. Sort of redundant. But it's a very large

00:02:14.371 --> 00:02:16.206
word that I learned. Redundant.

00:02:16.206 --> 00:02:19.473
IVAN: And someone clearly cast Bull's Strength on
those testicles.

00:02:19.473 --> 00:02:24.524
MATT: Ashly, who are you playing?

00:02:24.524 --> 00:02:26.803
ASHLY: I'm Piglet the barbarian.

00:02:26.803 --> 00:02:32.812
MATT: Delightful. Taliesin?

00:02:32.812 --> 00:02:34.750
TALIESIN: I'm Mezek the monk.

00:02:34.750 --> 00:02:40.003
MATT: Aw, this is going to be fun. Marisha.

00:02:40.003 --> 00:02:43.480
MARISHA: I'm Snizzler, the mad bombing alchemist!

00:02:43.480 --> 00:02:48.258
MATT: Oh, man. I'm already excited. And Ivan.

00:02:48.258 --> 00:02:55.412
IVAN: Grizznak Stompstork, reporting for duty.
Goblin fartmage, available to all of you. I am the

00:02:55.412 --> 00:02:57.812
brains of the bunch, as you can see.

00:02:57.812 --> 00:03:01.988
MATT: Perfect! This will be a fun adventure for
the evening.

00:03:01.988 --> 00:03:06.024
TALIESIN: You actually get to use the phrase,
"I've smelt it, now it's time that I dealt it."

00:03:06.024 --> 00:03:09.291
IVAN: Stolen, it will be used.

00:03:09.291 --> 00:03:12.018
TALIESIN: Yeah, take it. Public domain, public
domain. I'm sorry if I already stepped on that one.

00:03:12.018 --> 00:03:15.827
MATT: So we've got to go through a couple quick
announcements here and then we'll overview the game

00:03:15.827 --> 00:03:21.657
stuff. So for those watching, I want to remind you
that this Thursday is Critical Role's 50th

00:03:21.657 --> 00:03:27.075
episode. We're having a special episode to
commemorate this, a couple of surprises that we

00:03:27.075 --> 00:03:31.818
have in store for you guys, so definitely be there
at Thursday at 7:00pm Pacific to check out our

00:03:31.818 --> 00:03:35.879
50th episode. Marisha, you have a new episode of
Signal Boost tomorrow--

00:03:35.879 --> 00:03:44.381
MARISHA: Yes! Episode two of Hector! Which is
episode six of Signal Boost! Watch it.

00:03:44.381 --> 00:03:49.152
MATT: And having already seen it, this episode has
my favorite intro so far. I laughed for five solid

00:03:49.152 --> 00:03:51.477
minutes straight, so you'll enjoy it.

00:03:51.477 --> 00:03:54.857
MARISHA: It's very funny. Check it out, it's very
funny. Hector's funny.

00:03:54.857 --> 00:03:56.000
IVAN: Hector's the best.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:01.381
MATT: Indeed. So part of this whole event tonight,
with the folks at Pathfinder, Paizo, and

00:04:01.381 --> 00:04:05.208
Syrinscape, is in celebration of the upcoming
International Tabletop Day!

00:04:05.208 --> 00:04:06.639
(cheering)

00:04:06.639 --> 00:04:09.853
MATT: It is happening on April 30th, we'll be
doing a whole series of great events here in the

00:04:09.853 --> 00:04:13.584
studio throughout the day so mark it on your
calendars, get your friends together--

00:04:13.584 --> 00:04:16.852
IVAN: 24 hours of livestreaming.

00:04:16.852 --> 00:04:18.960
MATT: Yes! It's going to be great. It's going to
be great.

00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:21.327
ASHLY: For charity, right? For a good cause?

00:04:21.327 --> 00:04:27.939
IVAN: KaBOOM! kaboom.org, which is bringing play
back into the lives of children currently living

00:04:27.939 --> 00:04:30.791
in property, (scoffs) "in property." In poverty!

00:04:30.791 --> 00:04:34.178
MATT: Children who have been bricked into walls!
It's horrible!

00:04:34.178 --> 00:04:41.301
PHIL: They're stuck on estates! With nothing but
ponies. They need to play!

00:04:41.301 --> 00:04:45.138
IVAN: They're living amongst property, land is
surrounding them. No, guys, so currently kids

00:04:45.138 --> 00:04:49.042
living in poverty and they're trying to bring play
back into their lives, such as things like

00:04:49.042 --> 00:04:54.696
board games, and we're actually going to be giving
away a lot of board games to kaboom.org, part of

00:04:54.696 --> 00:04:58.700
your involvement during International Tabletop
Day, so don't miss it.

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:04.512
MATT: And if you'd like to plug what usually
occupies this spot on Mondays...?

00:05:04.512 --> 00:05:08.689
IVAN: Oh, well, if you're a Critical Role fan, or
if you're any kind of fan, and normally you're

00:05:08.689 --> 00:05:13.186
here Monday nights, then thank you for coming on
Monday night again. If you're not, and this a

00:05:13.186 --> 00:05:17.532
weird timeslot for you, we still play role-playing
games on Monday nights, they are just

00:05:17.532 --> 00:05:23.948
mini-campaigns instead of the epic, long
brainchild of Matt Mercer's amazing imagination,

00:05:23.948 --> 00:05:29.283
instead we do little one-offs, like we just got
done playing "Army of Darkness" which was then

00:05:29.283 --> 00:05:37.258
created by chat, it was coined "The Arby's of
Darkness," because their last stand was in the

00:05:37.258 --> 00:05:41.164
middle of an Arby's restaurant which one of the
characters managed. And officially--

00:05:41.164 --> 00:05:42.256
MARISHA: That's amazing

00:05:42.256 --> 00:05:43.396
IVAN: It was pretty cool.

00:05:43.396 --> 00:05:45.719
TALIESIN: What meat is this? What meat is this?!

00:05:45.719 --> 00:05:50.500
IVAN: The deadites actually came out through the
portal at the very end of it, and they were all

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:53.520
the busboys, and the, "I'll swallow your soul,
I'll swallow your soul!"

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.762
TALIESIN: That's every Arby's I've ever been to.

00:05:55.762 --> 00:05:57.340
PHIL: Really, it's the same thing.

00:05:57.340 --> 00:06:01.175
IVAN: And the next campaign that we're going to be
doing officially/unofficially, is going to be

00:06:01.175 --> 00:06:08.048
"Pugmire," which is a new game, it's basically 5th
edition in a world of fantasy dogs. It's

00:06:08.048 --> 00:06:09.411
a post-apocalyptic future--

00:06:09.411 --> 00:06:12.372
MARISHA: I was going to make a joke about that,
and then it was the real thing, so--

00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:16.194
IVAN: It exists. It's in the future, in which all
man has been wiped out and now dogs reign supreme,

00:06:16.194 --> 00:06:20.797
and they have formed a church called, "The Church
of Man," in which they have a code of laws, the

00:06:20.797 --> 00:06:27.169
first law being, "Be a good dog." The second law
being, "Fetch what has been left behind," and the

00:06:27.169 --> 00:06:32.549
third being, I believe it's, "Bite only those who
attack you." So it's great--

00:06:32.549 --> 00:06:35.138
ASHLY: I'm imagining Mad Max with dogs, in my mind
now.

00:06:35.138 --> 00:06:37.217
IVAN: But it's fantasy, it's still fantasy.

00:06:37.217 --> 00:06:46.764
IVAN: So you could be like, a pincer cleric, or
you could be a dachshund rogue or something like that.

00:06:46.764 --> 00:06:47.953
MATT: That's fantastic.

00:06:47.953 --> 00:06:50.558
IVAN: So 7:00-10:00pm usually on Mondays, come
hang out.

00:06:50.558 --> 00:06:57.255
MATT: Do it. Check it out, guys. It's pretty
fantastic. So, another cool thing about having

00:06:57.255 --> 00:07:03.061
Paizo, the folks from Pathfinder here, is we have
a bunch of giveaways to give out throughout the

00:07:03.061 --> 00:07:05.148
evening to all you guys in chat.

00:07:05.148 --> 00:07:09.968
MARISHA: Like, there's a bag of stuff. I don't
even know what it is. It's exciting.

00:07:09.968 --> 00:07:11.378
TALIESIN: I think that's edamame.

00:07:11.378 --> 00:07:18.855
MATT: First off, you guys can go to
paizo.com/goblins, and store.syrinscape.com/geek

00:07:18.855 --> 00:07:24.052
to get 25% off a number of their goblin goods and
stuff as part of tonight's promotional thing. Go

00:07:24.052 --> 00:07:27.672
check it out, a lot of cool things there to grab.
But throughout the evening we'll be giving away

00:07:27.672 --> 00:07:33.461
small giveaways that include Pathfinder Core
rulebook pdfs in chat, the "Burnt Offerings

00:07:33.461 --> 00:07:40.386
Adventure" pdf, the soundset from Syrinscape that
