01:10:29.580 --> 01:10:32.011
MATT: All right, so as you two are there right in
front of it, the thing begins reforming the front

01:10:32.011 --> 01:10:35.949
of it, which is currently blown open from the bomb
that Snizzler left in there. It begins to shift

01:10:35.949 --> 01:10:40.564
and slither towards both of you guys and intending
to engulf you as well. I need you both to go ahead

01:10:40.564 --> 01:10:41.918
and make reflex saving throws.

01:10:41.918 --> 01:10:43.432
MARISHA: Oh man.

01:10:43.432 --> 01:10:51.016
ASHLY: No! I got seven. Do I get to know what the
result would be before I use my song?

01:10:51.016 --> 01:10:52.460
IVAN: You just get to reroll.

01:10:52.460 --> 01:10:54.980
MATT: You don't know what the result is, but do
you want to use your song now?

01:10:54.980 --> 01:10:57.709
MARISHA: Is that adding your reflex?

01:10:57.709 --> 01:11:00.763
ASHLY: I had a seven. Yeah, adding my reflex.

01:11:00.763 --> 01:11:01.998
MARISHA: Adding your reflex.

01:11:01.998 --> 01:11:04.392
MATT: What'd you get? Browntooth?

01:11:04.392 --> 01:11:10.724
PHIL: I got a 19 plus nine. 28.

01:11:10.724 --> 01:11:13.620
MATT: Okay, you dart out of the way into the
groove here as it moves forward.

01:11:13.620 --> 01:11:15.705
PHIL: Which is what I was planning to do anyway.

01:11:15.705 --> 01:11:20.664
MATT: So as you duck, as it begins to shift
forward, Piglet, in a moment of intensity, staring

01:11:20.664 --> 01:11:30.533
into the face of this for the first time, probably
your entire life, you're like, I can die. What?

01:11:30.533 --> 01:11:31.702
What are you going to do?

01:11:31.702 --> 01:11:34.664
ASHLY: I decide, no, I'm going to live forever,
and I'll sing my song.

01:11:34.664 --> 01:11:36.032
MATT: All right, go for it. What's your song?

01:11:36.032 --> 01:11:39.942
ASHLY: Okay. I'm going to try a thing. I don't
know if it's going to work.

01:11:39.942 --> 01:11:41.114
MATT: All right.

01:11:41.114 --> 01:11:46.740
ASHLY: I'm going to try to sing my song to the
tune of Kiss from a Rose. Because that's my go-to.

01:11:46.740 --> 01:11:50.594
TALIESIN: You're my favorite. Oh god.

01:11:50.594 --> 01:12:08.976
ASHLY: Let's see. (sings) Piglet, twitchy scratch
the rash until she sees them loud. Love trash,

01:12:08.976 --> 01:12:16.035
lift the hammer down and crash. Piglet angry time
to smash. Sorry.

01:12:16.035 --> 01:12:20.790
MATT: Well done. So go ahead and reroll your
reflex.

01:12:20.790 --> 01:12:23.044
IVAN: Please post those lyrics at some point.

01:12:23.044 --> 01:12:24.533
ASHLY: I got a two again.

01:12:24.533 --> 01:12:25.898
TALIESIN: No!

01:12:25.898 --> 01:12:28.334
ASHLY: I am going to die.

01:12:28.334 --> 01:12:31.715
PHIL: I mean, it wasn't a very good song.

01:12:31.715 --> 01:12:34.525
MARISHA: Fuck you, Seal. Fuck you.

01:12:34.525 --> 01:12:37.444
ASHLY: No! Shit.

01:12:37.444 --> 01:12:42.615
MATT: The creature has now engulfed both Piglet
and you get pulled up right next to it, jammed

01:12:42.615 --> 01:12:49.220
into the currently paralyzed Grizznak. I need you
to go ahead and make a fortitude saving throw.

01:12:49.220 --> 01:12:52.687
ASHLY: Oh my. Okay. It's the 20?

01:12:52.687 --> 01:12:59.113
TALIESIN: Here. Go nuts. That's the serious
business die.

01:12:59.113 --> 01:13:00.863
ASHLY: 14.

01:13:00.863 --> 01:13:02.469
TALIESIN: There we go.

01:13:02.469 --> 01:13:03.716
ASHLY: 19.

01:13:03.716 --> 01:13:05.161
This is beautiful.

01:13:05.161 --> 01:13:06.837
TALIESIN: Thank you. That's the angry die.

01:13:06.837 --> 01:13:08.349
ASHLY: That's the goddammit die.

01:13:08.349 --> 01:13:10.931
PHIL: Goddammit, don't die.

01:13:10.931 --> 01:13:16.633
MATT: And as you're pulled into it, trying to find
your way through, you get pulled into the thing,

01:13:16.633 --> 01:13:22.423
and you feel like that same numb sensation all
across. Which, by the way, your goblin song maybe

01:13:22.423 --> 01:13:26.030
missed a few vowels because of the blahlah, but
the rest of your body begins to tingle and you

01:13:26.030 --> 01:13:28.617
begin to fight against it and your body won't
move.

01:13:28.617 --> 01:13:29.859
MARISHA: No!

01:13:29.859 --> 01:13:31.385
MATT: Your body's paralyzed for six rounds.

01:13:31.385 --> 01:13:32.969
PHIL: Only six.

01:13:32.969 --> 01:13:39.262
MATT: Jammed up against-- However, it does take
another d6 points of fire damage from your bomb. So

01:13:39.262 --> 01:13:43.084
go ahead and roll that if you could.

01:13:43.084 --> 01:13:44.402
MARISHA: Four.

01:13:44.402 --> 01:13:49.766
MATT: Four points of fire damage. All righty. All
right, that brings us back to the top, Browntooth,

01:13:49.766 --> 01:13:52.257
you're up. You dodge to the side. You see it
engulf--

01:13:52.257 --> 01:13:55.903
PHIL: Is it moving away from me?

01:13:55.903 --> 01:13:59.929
MATT: It is. It moved this way and you sidestep
and it's moving parallel to you.

01:13:59.929 --> 01:14:04.295
PHIL: Okay. I would like to get behind it and
shoot my crossbow.

01:14:04.295 --> 01:14:07.039
MATT: Okay. So you move--

01:14:07.039 --> 01:14:12.419
PHIL: Because I've decided I don't want any more
hand-to-hand combat. Seems like a bad idea.

01:14:12.419 --> 01:14:15.530
MATT: A pseudopod swings out towards you but you--
it misses you entirely. As you dart backward with

01:14:15.530 --> 01:14:18.729
your crossbow loaded, you take aim and go ahead
and fire.

01:14:18.729 --> 01:14:29.647
PHIL: This one, right? Fuck. Seven plus nine. 16.

01:14:29.647 --> 01:14:35.419
MATT: You've heard the term "couldn't hit the
broad side of a barn"? Thankfully, this creature

01:14:35.419 --> 01:14:42.363
is the size of a barn. You manage to sink the bolt
into it. Go ahead and roll damage. You feel a

01:14:42.363 --> 01:14:48.011
slight bit of pain at your back as a bolt nips you
in the butt. But you can't do anything about it

01:14:48.011 --> 01:14:58.245
because you're paralyzed. Five points of damage.
All right. You guys can see the creature's shaking

01:14:58.245 --> 01:15:01.695
and shimmering as it's moving forward. It's having
a hard time keeping its form together, it's

01:15:01.695 --> 01:15:05.274
looking really rough as it's slowly dissolving
your two friends.

01:15:05.274 --> 01:15:08.316
MARISHA: Burn! Fire!

01:15:08.316 --> 01:15:11.102
MATT: All right, that's going to go ahead and
bring us to Mezek.

01:15:11.102 --> 01:15:15.002
TALIESIN: I am going to charge it with my
quarterstaff and hit it with a flurry of blows. I

01:15:15.002 --> 01:15:16.654
don't have any Ki points right now, do I?

01:15:16.654 --> 01:15:24.961
MATT: No because you are sober-- You require a
full round action to do flurry of bros. (laughs)

01:15:24.961 --> 01:15:26.502
MARISHA: Fury of bros? (laughs)

01:15:26.502 --> 01:15:28.722
PHIL : Fury of bros, (screams) yeah dude!

01:15:28.722 --> 01:15:30.525
TALIESIN: Okay, so I can't make a movement.

01:15:30.525 --> 01:15:35.803
MATT: You are two squares away from it, so in
order to get into it you would have to do a full

01:15:35.803 --> 01:15:37.929
round action.

01:15:37.929 --> 01:15:49.269
TALIESIN: Okay, I'll take the-- I'll take a nice
big, flying swing with my stick.

01:15:49.269 --> 01:15:51.875
MATT: Go for it.

01:15:51.875 --> 01:15:55.568
TALIESIN: (goblin screech) That's 13.

01:15:55.568 --> 01:15:57.585
MATT: 13 hits, go ahead and roll damage.

01:15:57.585 --> 01:16:03.597
TALIESIN: God damn. That's seven. Seven points of
damage.

01:16:03.597 --> 01:16:05.829
MATT: Seven points of damage--

01:16:05.829 --> 01:16:08.678
How do you want to do this?

01:16:08.678 --> 01:16:14.356
TALIESIN: I want to, screaming bloody murder,
squish it and splash it with the stick like you

01:16:14.356 --> 01:16:18.438
were trying to hit a rat scurrying around on the
ground, and I don't care, once it's gone, I'm

01:16:18.438 --> 01:16:23.807
going to keep hitting them. I'm going to keep
slapping and slapping until it's mush.

01:16:23.807 --> 01:16:29.815
MATT: Okay. You guys watch as Mezek goes batshit
insane on this cube, smacks into the side, manages

01:16:29.815 --> 01:16:33.480
to hit a core of its form where some of the bones
are floating inside from previous victims.

01:16:33.480 --> 01:16:37.514
Probably the shiny things you saw earlier, the
person that once wore it, bits of them are

01:16:37.514 --> 01:16:43.852
floating inside. As it begins to collapse on
itself like an order of cold flan and as it

01:16:43.852 --> 01:16:48.309
liquefies, part of it pouring into the cistern,
the two of their bodies are starting to be pulled

01:16:48.309 --> 01:16:51.311
into the cistern with its form, unable to keep
shape.

01:16:51.311 --> 01:16:52.567
ASHLY: Help! Help! Help!

01:16:52.567 --> 01:16:53.857
TALIESIN: I run in and grab them!

01:16:53.857 --> 01:16:57.365
MARISHA: Yeah, I help as well. Oh, Grizz!

01:16:57.365 --> 01:17:01.853
MATT: Okay. You guys grab them, pull them out onto
the side. The last bit of the flaming corpse of

01:17:01.853 --> 01:17:08.598
this cube sloshes into the cistern. You wait about
another minute or so before you both get your

01:17:08.598 --> 01:17:09.956
bodies back.

01:17:09.956 --> 01:17:15.463
MARISHA: I take a little goo out of his ear and
I-- Ah, yeah, it's got a little kick there, yeah,

01:17:15.463 --> 01:17:16.770
you're right.

01:17:16.770 --> 01:17:22.899
IVAN: I take my nose and go-- and I watch as goo
goes (wet noise) out of my ears.

01:17:22.899 --> 01:17:27.365
ASHLY: Is this what being greased feels like?
Because I don't like it.

01:17:27.365 --> 01:17:28.603
TALIESIN: It's not easy--

01:17:28.603 --> 01:17:30.323
ASHLY, PHIL and TALIESIN: Being greased.

01:17:30.323 --> 01:17:39.713
MATT: So as you're resting up from this, do you
guys need to do anything to heal up a bit?

01:17:39.713 --> 01:17:43.724
IVAN: If we had things in which to heal up with,
but as of course--

01:17:43.724 --> 01:17:46.254
MARISHA: Do we get any healing surges or anything
like that?

01:17:46.254 --> 01:17:49.085
MATT: No. This is Pathfinder, girl.

01:17:49.085 --> 01:17:53.657
IVAN: This is not like fourth edition. I don't
think we have anything because I certainly didn't

01:17:53.657 --> 01:17:55.280
take it and we have no real--

01:17:55.280 --> 01:17:59.691
TALIESIN: I have the healing skill, can we try and
use the healing skill to reset things?

01:17:59.691 --> 01:18:06.965
MATT: Sure I'll let you do that, being the monk
that you are.

01:18:06.965 --> 01:18:15.606
PHIL: When they say it couldn't hurt, I'm not sure
they're right.

01:18:15.606 --> 01:18:17.831
TALIESIN: 20!

01:18:17.831 --> 01:18:23.575
MATT: 20? And with that, with the various burn
wounds on your body, from the acid that's burned

01:18:23.575 --> 01:18:28.982
away and parts of the actual burn damage you've
taken from the explosion, Mezek rushes in and like

01:18:28.982 --> 01:18:31.102
the roughest masseuse you've ever seen--

01:18:31.102 --> 01:18:33.106
IVAN: It's like the best shiatsu massage I've ever
gotten.

01:18:33.106 --> 01:18:40.164
TALIESIN: Let go! Let go! You're holding a lot of
tension!

01:18:40.164 --> 01:18:45.371
IVAN: Ugh, that's good, that one right there. That
knot especially.

01:18:45.371 --> 01:18:47.635
PHIL: Don't forget to breathe.

01:18:47.635 --> 01:18:54.806
MATT: I'd say for that, go ahead and heal four
points due to the rhythmic massage of Mezek's

01:18:54.806 --> 01:18:56.852
rough and tumble goblin hands.

01:18:56.852 --> 01:19:05.960
IVAN: I would like to point out that you just healed me
through a goblin shiatsu massage,

01:19:05.960 --> 01:19:07.233
that was amazing.

01:19:07.233 --> 01:19:08.868
MATT: Yes, yep that happened.

01:19:08.868 --> 01:19:12.842
TALIESIN: With vomit-based massage oil! It's
organic!

01:19:12.842 --> 01:19:14.366
ASHLY: Only the finest for you.

01:19:14.366 --> 01:19:20.651
IVAN: I step up and I crack my back a little bit
and okay. We're good to go. Let's do this.

01:19:20.651 --> 01:19:25.786
TALIESIN: Do any of my flasks or jugs have any
liquor in them?

01:19:25.786 --> 01:19:28.295
MATT: No. However, make a perception check.

01:19:28.295 --> 01:19:33.137
ASHLY: I also have a jug, I don't know what's in
it.

01:19:33.137 --> 01:19:34.183
TALIESIN: 20.

01:19:34.183 --> 01:19:41.222
MATT: 20. You have a jug, it's mainly sloshing
water and grime, your usual-- what you like to sip

01:19:41.222 --> 01:19:44.927
on the way of your journey. Whatever you find
along the way. You guys are into this whole

01:19:44.927 --> 01:19:48.270
scavenging thing. As you're thinking about this,
ah, you didn't bring any alcohol,

01:19:48.270 --> 01:19:50.864
you smell alcohol.

01:19:50.864 --> 01:19:55.237
TALIESIN: (sniffs) Happy juice. Happy juice!

01:19:55.237 --> 01:20:00.660
MATT: All of a sudden you guys watch as Mezek
darts down the path--

01:20:00.660 --> 01:20:06.496
IVAN: Follow him! He found booze, which means when
there's booze there's stuff and a happy Mezek.

01:20:06.496 --> 01:20:08.092
MARISHA: Yeah, I like that.

01:20:08.092 --> 01:20:13.649
MATT: As you dart ahead, you come to the edge, and
you can see there the path continues for another

01:20:13.649 --> 01:20:18.083
200 feet before it dips off, but you don't know
quite where. But the scent is strong here and you

01:20:18.083 --> 01:20:24.058
look over and you can see the wall to your
immediate right actually has a fissure in it. A

01:20:24.058 --> 01:20:28.437
part of it has cracked or a part of it has
semi-eroded away. And you can see the very distant

01:20:28.437 --> 01:20:30.510
dark glimmer of something beyond it.

01:20:30.510 --> 01:20:33.227
TALIESIN: I stick my hand in and go for it.

01:20:33.227 --> 01:20:34.954
MATT: Go ahead and make a strength check.

01:20:34.954 --> 01:20:39.618
TALIESIN: That's not funny. Eight.

01:20:39.618 --> 01:20:44.859
MATT: Eight. You go and grab the stone, you
lift your whole goblin body up on it and start pulling. You

01:20:44.954 --> 01:20:48.398
guys catch up and see Mezek fighting with this
wall and making no headway whatsoever.

01:20:48.398 --> 01:20:50.211
TALIESIN: Piglet! Piglet!

01:20:50.211 --> 01:20:52.410
ASHLY: Okay, let me smash this with the hammer.

01:20:52.410 --> 01:20:57.155
IVAN: I was going to say, I'm going to grab
Mezek's waist and help him pull, so that we're just

01:20:57.155 --> 01:20:59.471
two goblins pulling on it now.

01:20:59.471 --> 01:21:02.403
MATT: (laughs) Okay, so you guys are just like
double-pulling on it. You make a strength check

01:21:02.403 --> 01:21:04.145
as well. Go ahead and roll an attack against the
wall.

01:21:04.145 --> 01:21:06.105
MARISHA: Is Mezek getting in a fight with a
wall again?

01:21:06.105 --> 01:21:07.955
IVAN: He does this, just humor him.

01:21:07.993 --> 01:21:09.361
PHIL: He usually loses.

01:21:09.361 --> 01:21:12.558
ASHLY: 17? Is this plus strength?

01:21:12.558 --> 01:21:14.034
TALIESIN: Plus strength modifier.

01:21:14.034 --> 01:21:19.574
MATT: Well, go ahead and roll damage because you
hit the wall. Outside of a critical fail,

01:21:19.574 --> 01:21:21.222
you're fine.

01:21:21.222 --> 01:21:23.383
ASHLY: So should I do my normal?

01:21:23.383 --> 01:21:28.173
MATT: Yes, a normal d10 plus-- you're not raging,
so that would be a plus four.

01:21:28.173 --> 01:21:29.669
ASHLY: Five.

01:21:29.669 --> 01:21:37.172
MATT: Five points of damage. As you guys are
pulling, the hammer comes down as Piglet smashes

01:21:37.172 --> 01:21:42.920
into the side of this wall. The stones crumble inward and
you both go flung forward into the darkness,

01:21:42.920 --> 01:21:48.836
tumbling over each other before you both (impact
noise) against the wall, slowly slide down. As you

01:21:48.836 --> 01:21:57.242
look around, you're inside this darkened chamber.
Glancing around you, first off you immediately

01:21:57.242 --> 01:21:59.537
notice that there is a heavy smell of alcohol in
this room.

01:21:59.537 --> 01:22:05.732
IVAN: We're in one of those, humans call them a
"Ta-vern" or one--

01:22:05.732 --> 01:22:10.944
MARISHA: This is one of those cel-lar. Cel-lar?

01:22:10.944 --> 01:22:16.678
IVAN: It's, yeah, it's where they do their
fighting at. It's basically where humans go to

01:22:16.678 --> 01:22:18.519
beat up each other. It's a goblin pit!

01:22:18.519 --> 01:22:19.985
TALIESIN: Sounds like heaven.

01:22:19.985 --> 01:22:21.184
IVAN: It's amazing.

01:22:21.184 --> 01:22:24.017
ASHLY: I've heard they also "pick up chicks".
Whatever that means.

01:22:24.017 --> 01:22:25.616
TALIESIN: Baby chickens?

01:22:25.616 --> 01:22:31.583
ASHLY: (loudly) There are chickens here?! It's
like a "hoo-er house", right?

01:22:31.583 --> 01:22:36.771
PHIL: Do they eat owls, too? Chickens and owls?
I'm getting hungry!

01:22:36.771 --> 01:22:38.184
TALIESIN: Baby owls!

01:22:38.184 --> 01:22:41.682
MATT: Which, as you guys are getting hungry, you
look around this chamber you're in, you see a sack

01:22:41.682 --> 01:22:52.562
of moldy grains, small containers of salts and
spices, dried meats that are put on racks against the wall,

01:22:52.562 --> 01:22:57.577
casks and bottles of wine, and ale all throughout
this--

01:22:57.577 --> 01:22:59.407
TALIESIN: Done. Ale? Done. Going for the ale.

01:22:59.407 --> 01:23:04.080
IVAN: We forgot about our mission for as long as
it takes for us to eat everything in this cellar.

01:23:04.080 --> 01:23:09.653
MATT: You guys go nuts! Devouring everything,
grabbing at meat, filling your bellies. You'd

01:23:09.653 --> 01:23:11.868
be welcome to fill your jugs with alcohol--

01:23:11.868 --> 01:23:13.701
TALIESIN: I'm filling my flask and my waterskin.

01:23:13.701 --> 01:23:16.948
MATT: Do you clear out your
jug first, or are you just going to add to it?

01:23:17.338 --> 01:23:19.489
TALIESIN: No, I'm just going to add it.

01:23:19.489 --> 01:23:21.000
MATT: All right, cool.

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:23.553
IVAN: Does this help me at all with my current hit
point situation?

01:23:23.553 --> 01:23:25.324
MARISHA: Eat up, maybe?

01:23:25.324 --> 01:23:32.621
MATT: For the circumstances here, you heal
one hit point from the food--

01:23:32.621 --> 01:23:36.387
TALIESIN: We all heal one?

01:23:36.387 --> 01:23:45.875
IVAN: But yeah, I will eat it all, if anything it
will allow me to feel better.

01:23:45.875 --> 01:23:48.955
MATT: I will say, if you want to go ahead and tear
into that moldy grain, that might heal you a

01:23:48.955 --> 01:23:52.891
little more, but it looks like your stomach might
have a rough time with it.

01:23:52.891 --> 01:23:54.122
Do you want to go for it?

01:23:54.122 --> 01:23:56.630
TALIESIN: Maybe you have to have a chat with a
spirit animal.

01:23:56.630 --> 01:23:57.907
IVAN: I'm a god damn goblin.

01:23:57.907 --> 01:23:59.293
TALIESIN: Nothing bad happens when you eat moldy
grain.

01:23:59.293 --> 01:24:01.010
MATT: You get on top of that moldy grain, you tear
into it, you destroy it--

01:24:01.010 --> 01:24:07.500
IVAN: I'm going to-- at one point I'm going to take
one of the pots and I'm going to scoop it, and I'm

01:24:07.500 --> 01:24:13.956
going to pour it over my head because I know that
moldy grain has healing properties. And as I put

01:24:13.956 --> 01:24:17.982
it into my mouth I'm going to rub it all over my
burning sores.

01:24:17.982 --> 01:24:21.389
PHIL: I call you Grizznak the Glutinous.

01:24:21.389 --> 01:24:22.842
(laughter)

01:24:22.842 --> 01:24:25.597
TALIESIN: I'm imagining Orson Welles at the end of
Apocalypse Now! right now, with the towel--

01:24:25.597 --> 01:24:33.655
IVAN: Also Arcane Mark on the cellar wall, Goblin
Dickbutt, Grizznak the Great has been here.

01:24:33.655 --> 01:24:39.907
MATT: As you go ahead and focus over on the wall,
you hear this rumbling in your stomach. Go ahead

