01:51:06.327 --> 01:51:11.534
you like, you cross your arms and look around,
just so everyone else understands that it wasn't you.

01:51:11.534 --> 01:51:12.959
IVAN: Good try, Piglet.

01:51:12.959 --> 01:51:17.721
MATT: (splashing) Into the water below.

01:51:17.721 --> 01:51:19.748
MARISHA: I hate water.

01:51:19.748 --> 01:51:22.209
PHIL: She really does.

01:51:22.209 --> 01:51:24.572
ASHLY: Hey. He didn't die.

01:51:24.572 --> 01:51:26.733
MATT: I do need you to make a swim check.

01:51:26.733 --> 01:51:39.602
MARISHA: I'm fucking terrible at swimming. Oh god.
Okay. Well, I rolled a 14 and I have a minus four,

01:51:39.602 --> 01:51:41.693
to my swim. So ten.

01:51:41.693 --> 01:51:47.874
MATT: So you're treading water and slowly making
your way across this giant cistern, about 20 feet

01:51:47.874 --> 01:51:54.304
below where they are. You get halfway across,
splashing. You guys see Snizzler trying to make

01:51:54.304 --> 01:51:56.346
her way over to where you guys are.

01:51:56.346 --> 01:51:59.127
IVAN: (laughing) There's water down there.

01:51:59.127 --> 01:52:01.251
MARISHA: Seriously, you guys.

01:52:01.251 --> 01:52:05.236
MATT: Roll another swim check to try and make it
the other half of the way.

01:52:05.236 --> 01:52:07.263
IVAN: Come on, Snizzler.

01:52:07.263 --> 01:52:12.036
MARISHA: Oh, that's better. 13.

01:52:12.036 --> 01:52:16.564
MATT: 13. You make your way up to the edge, like
(grunting). You guys can look down now and you can

01:52:16.564 --> 01:52:22.610
just barely see outside of your darkvision here,
you see Snizzler approach and is now treading

01:52:22.610 --> 01:52:24.645
water at the bottom of the cistern below you.

01:52:24.645 --> 01:52:26.886
ASHLY: We'll lower the ropes, Snizz.

01:52:26.886 --> 01:52:33.850
MARISHA: Come on. Can I see if I can find purchase
on a little rock? Off to the side, I can hold onto.

01:52:33.850 --> 01:52:36.877
MATT: Yeah. You go over and reach over and you
grab a rock and pull onto it and pull your weight

01:52:36.877 --> 01:52:41.775
up and your fingers slip off of it. There is a
slick liquid from general grime.

01:52:41.775 --> 01:52:43.185
IVAN: Grab the rope.

01:52:43.185 --> 01:52:46.231
MARISHA: Come on! Come on.

01:52:46.231 --> 01:52:47.370
TALIESIN: I drop the rope.

01:52:47.370 --> 01:52:50.264
MATT: Okay. The rope (thumps) into the water next
to you. You grab onto it and the rest of you guys

01:52:50.264 --> 01:52:54.708
slowly pull Snizzler back up onto the
entranceway.

01:52:54.708 --> 01:53:00.775
IVAN: My turn. My turn. I want to be thrown next.
My turn.

01:53:00.775 --> 01:53:04.569
TALIESIN: I'm going to look at the ceiling. I want
to see if there is anywhere we can attach the rope

01:53:04.569 --> 01:53:06.444
to the ceiling to make a swing.

01:53:06.444 --> 01:53:12.595
MATT: Currently, it is a dome, a smooth stone dome
that then has three openings where the rainwater

01:53:12.595 --> 01:53:15.164
is pouring into currently and filling the bottom
of the cistern.

01:53:15.164 --> 01:53:18.744
ASHLY: So the only way up is basically those
little stones? That we can see.

01:53:18.744 --> 01:53:24.353
IVAN: The only other thing I can think of, taking
my Snizzler hat off for a sec-- er, my Grizznak--

01:53:24.353 --> 01:53:32.013
is I could potentially Mage Hand up the rope. But
I don't think I can tie it, I can just move it up.

01:53:32.013 --> 01:53:37.123
PHIL: You know what? No, I'll climb up and tie the
rope. And everyone else can climb.

01:53:37.123 --> 01:53:38.915
IVAN: We'll catch you if you fall.

01:53:38.915 --> 01:53:44.900
PHIL: Right. That'll happen. I climb up to the
grate, with the rope.

01:53:44.900 --> 01:53:47.525
MATT: Okay. Go ahead and roll a climb check.

01:53:47.525 --> 01:53:55.000
PHIL: 12 plus climb. 18.

01:53:55.000 --> 01:54:01.903
MATT: 18. As you pull yourself up (grunting) and
it is a slight curvature, so you're, like, hanging

01:54:01.903 --> 01:54:08.083
and holding onto it, but in true goblin Tom Cruise
fashion, keeping a stern expression on your face.

01:54:08.083 --> 01:54:10.264
PHIL: Well, you know Tom Cruise is a goblin.
That's why he's so small.

01:54:10.264 --> 01:54:12.180
MATT: Makes sense. Hopping on the sofa.

01:54:12.180 --> 01:54:15.293
PHIL: (goblin noise) I'm in love. I'm in love. I'm
in love.

01:54:15.293 --> 01:54:22.017
MATT: As you pull yourself up, tiny goblin feet
dangling below, keeping your focus, Browntooth,

01:54:22.017 --> 01:54:28.167
you bring your way across the ceiling, carrying
that rope in your grin. You get up to the edge of

01:54:28.167 --> 01:54:33.698
where the water's currently pouring into the
cistern and it's moving past, I need you to roll

01:54:33.698 --> 01:54:36.519
another climb check to try and keep holding.

01:54:36.519 --> 01:54:38.909
PHIL: Nine.

01:54:38.909 --> 01:54:42.549
MATT: Nine. Your fingers are starting to slip.
You're starting to slip.

01:54:42.549 --> 01:54:47.018
IVAN: Can I cast Open on the grate and see if
it'll maybe lift him up with it open?

01:54:47.018 --> 01:54:49.851
MATT: Yeah. You know what, for a--

01:54:49.851 --> 01:54:51.654
IVAN: Do you want me to grab it?

01:54:51.654 --> 01:54:54.842
MATT: Yeah. Let's see if we can. What's the spell?
This is Open?

01:54:54.842 --> 01:54:55.960
IVAN: Open.

01:54:55.960 --> 01:55:01.443
ASHLY: I'd just like to take this moment to say
that Browntooth is clearly the coolest goblin of

01:55:01.443 --> 01:55:02.841
all the goblins.

01:55:02.841 --> 01:55:04.066
(laughter)

01:55:04.066 --> 01:55:09.633
ASHLY: He transcends space and time and climbed
a slippery wall with a rope in his mouth.

01:55:09.633 --> 01:55:10.993
PHIL: Almost climbed.

01:55:10.993 --> 01:55:12.579
MARISHA: The rest of us are total degenerates.

01:55:12.579 --> 01:55:15.196
ASHLY: I'm just throwing people, like--

01:55:15.196 --> 01:55:22.082
MATT: Yeah, there's no resistance to it. As you're
slipping, slipping, all of a sudden the grate that

01:55:22.082 --> 01:55:30.214
contains the water opens and actually slams into
your side, but you manage to catch onto it. It

01:55:30.214 --> 01:55:36.742
knocks the wind out of you, but you manage to hold
on the edge. You catch your breath and you realize

01:55:36.742 --> 01:55:41.655
this is, first off, holding your weight, and
second, there's a number of cross iron bars that

01:55:41.655 --> 01:55:44.692
are all welded together that would be a good place
probably to tie the rope off.

01:55:44.692 --> 01:55:48.022
PHIL: I think I will tie the rope to the things
that would make a good place to tie the rope.

01:55:48.022 --> 01:55:49.632
IVAN: You're welcome!

01:55:49.632 --> 01:55:54.236
PHIL: Yeah, right. I saved your life, you saved
mine-- twice.

01:55:54.236 --> 01:55:58.428
IVAN Well, you know what? Now we've got one left.

01:55:58.428 --> 01:56:00.520
PHIL: One left.

01:56:00.520 --> 01:56:07.143
IVAN: Which means I owe you a bird. (sings) Birdy
bird bird bird bird. Bird for you, bird for me.

01:56:07.143 --> 01:56:11.731
Two birds for you and one bird for me. Smash it,
twist it, turn it in a stew. Stick it in your face

01:56:11.731 --> 01:56:14.208
and you love-- and I love you.

01:56:14.208 --> 01:56:16.068
MARISHA: I love that song.

01:56:16.068 --> 01:56:17.325
PHIL: He's got many songs.

01:56:17.325 --> 01:56:18.681
TALIESIN: Very impressive.

01:56:18.681 --> 01:56:23.812
MATT As you finish tying the rope, helping each
person up, each of you manage to climb, having it

01:56:23.812 --> 01:56:27.987
tossed back. It takes you a while to get going,
but you do manage to--

01:56:27.987 --> 01:56:31.150
PHIL We've now been on this quest for five days.

01:56:31.150 --> 01:56:37.801
TALIESIN In my head it's all Henson puppets, and
it's adorable. It's like Fraggle Rock, I'm there.

01:56:37.801 --> 01:56:41.142
(cheering)

01:56:41.142 --> 01:56:45.314
ASHLY: The other goblin crew has already made it,
they've got the stone, they're back. That's what's

01:56:45.314 --> 01:56:48.194
already happened in my head. I'll be disappointed
if that's not what happens.

01:56:48.194 --> 01:56:51.723
MATT: In climbing up the side of the grate,
however, going on the other side, you are now

01:56:51.723 --> 01:56:55.527
fighting against the torrent of water so I need
each of you to make a climb check.

01:56:55.527 --> 01:56:57.575
MARISHA: Oh we're all doing this?

01:56:57.575 --> 01:56:58.648
TALIESIN: Yeah, yeah.

01:56:58.648 --> 01:57:00.664
MATT: You don't have to, you can stay back in the
sewers.

01:57:00.664 --> 01:57:02.965
PHIL: Wait for the fire to come.

01:57:02.965 --> 01:57:04.545
ASHLY: 14.

01:57:04.545 --> 01:57:06.889
MARISHA: Oh my god.

01:57:06.889 --> 01:57:08.958
PHIL: 16.

01:57:08.958 --> 01:57:10.092
TALIESIN: Nine.

01:57:10.092 --> 01:57:12.055
MARISHA: Three?

01:57:12.055 --> 01:57:15.069
MATT; (laughing) What do you have, Grizznak?

01:57:15.069 --> 01:57:16.678
IVAN: Two.

01:57:16.678 --> 01:57:18.734
MATT Two? Okay. So--

01:57:18.734 --> 01:57:24.151
PHIL: Who do we have to save now?

01:57:24.151 --> 01:57:33.141
MATT: We'll say for the sake of brevity here, an
additional hour or so is spent perpetually

01:57:33.141 --> 01:57:38.238
retrieving your allies who keep getting all the
way up and then (splash) right into the water. But

01:57:38.238 --> 01:57:43.806
you have to admire the tenacity.

01:57:43.806 --> 01:57:46.936
TALIESIN: I drink everything in my flask at this
point.

01:57:46.936 --> 01:57:49.391
MATT: Okay, so you get your Ki point going.

01:57:49.391 --> 01:57:50.965
TALIESIN: I've got to keep drinking.

01:57:50.965 --> 01:57:56.041
MATT: Eventually you guys make your way up past
the flowing of water, which has slowed now, and

01:57:56.041 --> 01:57:58.728
that's probably how you're able to do it.

01:57:58.728 --> 01:58:01.510
TALIESIN: Someone upstairs finally jiggled the
toilet.

01:58:01.510 --> 01:58:09.672
MATT: Yeah. You make your way up into an upper
sewage system, and you guys crawl through what is

01:58:09.672 --> 01:58:14.710
a much smaller series of pipes, to the point where
you as goblins still have to crawl to make your

01:58:14.710 --> 01:58:19.748
way through. The sludge is thicker here and what
little bit of rain is pouring through you manage

01:58:19.748 --> 01:58:27.056
to keep between your arms and legs. Eventually you
find your way into the bottom of some sort of a

01:58:27.056 --> 01:58:31.921
chamber that is filled with apparently human
waste.

01:58:31.921 --> 01:58:33.150
TALIESIN: Yes.

01:58:33.150 --> 01:58:38.006
ASHLY: The blue poop has to be here.

01:58:38.006 --> 01:58:46.555
MARISHA: I take the poop and I start making a ball
out of it and I light it to see how flammable it is.

01:58:46.555 --> 01:58:47.796
MATT: Okay.

01:58:47.796 --> 01:58:50.422
IVAN: This is totally logical.

01:58:50.422 --> 01:58:53.467
PHIL: If it were church people, they drink a lot,
so it should light up.

01:58:53.467 --> 01:59:01.772
MATT: Like the finest of candles, it does catch
fire and begins to burn slowly. It's not dry

01:59:01.772 --> 01:59:05.346
enough to catch-- we're having this conversation.

01:59:05.346 --> 01:59:08.506
TALIESIN: No, I'm really excited that this is a
thing that's happening right now.

01:59:08.506 --> 01:59:13.808
MATT: It would need to be suitably dried out to
work as proper fuel, but--

01:59:13.808 --> 01:59:21.112
MARISHA: Definitely lots of alcohol, lots of
drugs, yeah. I start packaging up some of the poop.

01:59:21.112 --> 01:59:22.155
MATT: All right.

01:59:22.155 --> 01:59:25.078
PHIL: I look for any sort of egress.

01:59:25.078 --> 01:59:27.109
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:59:27.109 --> 01:59:28.170
IVAN: Same.

01:59:28.170 --> 01:59:30.937
ASHLY: Why not, I'll do it too.

01:59:30.937 --> 01:59:32.335
IVAN: 16.

01:59:32.335 --> 01:59:33.525
PHIL: Eight.

01:59:33.525 --> 01:59:34.654
ASHLY: 18.

01:59:34.654 --> 01:59:41.414
MATT: All right. While you're collecting your
filthy prize, both Piglet and Grizznek, you guys

01:59:41.414 --> 01:59:49.290
look up and notice that there is a wooden or stone
ceiling, but a singular opening above you. Like a

01:59:49.290 --> 01:59:50.697
circular hole.

01:59:50.697 --> 01:59:55.704
IVAN: First, I would like to listen to see if
there's any stinky, stupid humans upstairs.

01:59:55.704 --> 01:59:58.750
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:59:58.750 --> 02:00:03.056
IVAN: (singing) Stinky stupid humans. Eight.

02:00:03.056 --> 02:00:06.051
PHIL: I love that game. Stinky stupid humans!

02:00:06.051 --> 02:00:11.703
IVAN: They're so dumb. Stinky stupid humans, but
they're fun-- to kill!

02:00:11.703 --> 02:00:19.889
MATT: You listen and you hear the muffled noises
of conversation as well. It sounds like there are

02:00:19.889 --> 02:00:26.144
a few different voices, though they're behind a
couple of walls from where you are.

02:00:26.144 --> 02:00:27.469
IVAN: So they're not straight above us?

02:00:27.469 --> 02:00:28.491
MATT: No.

02:00:28.491 --> 02:00:32.538
IVAN: I'm going to cast Open again on that
opening.

02:00:32.538 --> 02:00:35.538
MATT: Okay. You cast Open. The opening is open.

02:00:35.538 --> 02:00:37.242
(laughter)

02:00:37.242 --> 02:00:39.045
MATT: So the spell is a success!

02:00:39.045 --> 02:00:42.715
IVAN: Yes! I will climb up through the poop
chute.

02:00:42.715 --> 02:00:49.557
MATT: As you pull yourself up out of it, in a
wonderful medieval version of the Ghoulies VHS

02:00:49.557 --> 02:00:51.836
cover, you pull yourself out from--

02:00:51.836 --> 02:00:55.030
TALIESIN: Wow, we went back.

02:00:55.030 --> 02:00:59.905
MATT: Oh man, I couldn't go near toilets for years
because of that movie cover at the VHS store.

02:00:59.905 --> 02:01:04.178
IVAN: I stick my head up and I look through the
toilet seat and then I go (blows nose) and knock a

02:01:04.178 --> 02:01:06.104
huge chunk of poop out of my nostril.

02:01:06.104 --> 02:01:09.571
MATT: There you go. Glancing ahead, your Open
spell missed, but did hit the front of the

02:01:09.571 --> 02:01:17.671
outhouse which has currently swung open in the
mid-day, facing the window leading into the tavern

02:01:17.671 --> 02:01:20.667
that you guys nearly entered beforehand.

02:01:20.667 --> 02:01:22.372
IVAN: Oh. Close.

02:01:22.372 --> 02:01:29.186
MATT: Closes shut. However, it does appear to be
nestled in an alleyway on the outside of it. It's

02:01:29.186 --> 02:01:32.664
a very thin opening. You didn't see any people
actually in the alley. You saw the outside of a

02:01:32.664 --> 02:01:34.819
window and a street thoroughfare.

02:01:34.819 --> 02:01:36.642
IVAN: Mmm.

02:01:36.642 --> 02:01:37.821
PHIL: Where are we?

02:01:37.821 --> 02:01:45.418
IVAN: We're outside now. We seem to be in what the
humans use to get rid of all their precious waste.

02:01:45.418 --> 02:01:47.018
TALIESIN: We're inside an outhouse?

02:01:47.018 --> 02:01:50.918
PHIL: That sounds sort of oxymoronic.

02:01:50.918 --> 02:01:57.122
IVAN: We're in one of those redundant human cubes
in which humans go to poop inside of instead of

02:01:57.122 --> 02:02:00.202
doing it where they sleep, which is way more
practical.

02:02:00.202 --> 02:02:07.701
ASHLY: Wait, guys, those church things-- isn't
there like a symbol that people use, like a circle

02:02:07.701 --> 02:02:09.192
or like--?

02:02:09.192 --> 02:02:13.530
IVAN: Well, I say we get Browntooth up here and he
can go scout it out. Right, Browntooth?

02:02:13.530 --> 02:02:21.246
PHIL: If it keeps you from blowing things up, and
you setting anything on fire. Right, I climb up

02:02:21.246 --> 02:02:28.901
and go out the outhouse to stealthily move into the
street.

02:02:28.901 --> 02:02:32.205
MATT: All righty. So, as you--

02:02:32.205 --> 02:02:37.196
IVAN: Wait, wait, wait. I'm also going to cast
Penumbra on him.

02:02:37.196 --> 02:02:38.327
MATT: Okay.

02:02:38.327 --> 02:02:41.916
IVAN: So, Penumbra, it basically puts a permanent
shadow on him.

02:02:41.916 --> 02:02:45.279
PHIL: Oh. I thought it gave me a number from
before.

02:02:45.279 --> 02:02:47.065
(laughs)

02:02:47.065 --> 02:02:49.059
MATT: Go ahead and roll a stealth check, if you
could.

02:02:49.059 --> 02:02:56.505
IVAN: Makes it so that even light spells make him
still look like he's covered in shadow.

02:02:56.505 --> 02:02:58.705
PHIL: 32.

02:02:58.765 --> 02:03:01.875
MATT: All right. As you stumble into the shady
alley, looking about, you glance over the side of

02:03:01.875 --> 02:03:05.505
the window real fast into the tavern, and you do
see there are probably a dozen patrons in there.

02:03:05.505 --> 02:03:11.783
Some drinks being served, a guard at the door on
the inside. However, looking to your left, there

02:03:11.783 --> 02:03:16.058
the alleyway spills out into a main street
thoroughfare, and you can see people walking by,

02:03:16.058 --> 02:03:23.483
families with children. There's a general air of
jovial energy to it, and some people are wearing

02:03:23.483 --> 02:03:29.149
flower crowns on their heads. You can see
carts being put along the street. Seems like the

02:03:29.149 --> 02:03:34.439
festival you were told of, this terrible, human
festival seems to be in full swing. Go ahead and

02:03:34.439 --> 02:03:36.725
make a survival check.

02:03:36.725 --> 02:03:39.058
PHIL: 16.

02:03:39.058 --> 02:03:46.732
MATT: You come out to the edge of the alleyway,
glance about. First thing you notice is the sun in

02:03:46.732 --> 02:03:52.101
the sky. You were like "eh, it's probably
mid-day-ish". No, it's pushing toward sunset now.

02:03:52.101 --> 02:03:54.833
You probably have another hour of sunlight. So
you don't know how much longer this festival's

02:03:54.833 --> 02:03:59.219
going to be going. You spent quite a while getting
here and wandering the sewers.

02:03:59.219 --> 02:04:01.861
IVAN: As per typical goblin fashion.

02:04:01.861 --> 02:04:10.928
MATT: Indeed. However, you notice that everyone is
walking a certain direction. And, one, there are a

02:04:10.928 --> 02:04:21.727
number of carts that are going by. There are
currently unmanned, closed carts that would be

02:04:21.727 --> 02:04:28.996
used to sell fruit and fish. This being a port
town, fish is a big export here. And the alleyways

02:04:28.996 --> 02:04:33.209
that you came out of? There is a second alleyway
that offshoots from where the outhouse is that

02:04:33.209 --> 02:04:38.444
goes between the buildings off the main
thoroughfare. This is what you're able to gauge in

02:04:38.444 --> 02:04:39.901
your time out here.

02:04:39.901 --> 02:04:51.216
PHIL: I go back and tell them what I've seen. So
everybody's going that way.

02:04:51.216 --> 02:04:53.643
IVAN: We should probably go--

02:04:53.643 --> 02:04:57.461
ALL: That way?

02:04:57.461 --> 02:04:59.084
IVAN: That way.

02:04:59.084 --> 02:05:00.161
ASHLY: That way!

02:05:00.161 --> 02:05:07.002
MARISHA: Maybe if we get on each others' shoulders
with a coat, we'll look like peoples!

02:05:07.002 --> 02:05:14.733
ASHLY: I want do a perception roll for a big coat.
14.

02:05:14.733 --> 02:05:20.670
MATT: You glance over the window and look inside.
One of the bar patrons, sitting by the bar, is

02:05:20.670 --> 02:05:31.296
this rotund-looking gentleman in his late 40s.
Balding hair, a double chin, leaned forward on the

02:05:31.296 --> 02:05:35.975
bar, looking like he's ready to pass out from the
amount of alcohol he's been drinking. He is in the

02:05:35.975 --> 02:05:39.216
inside of the tavern. He has a very long coat that
drapes past the bar.

02:05:39.216 --> 02:05:43.024
ASHLY: We got to do it! There's no alternative!

02:05:43.024 --> 02:05:49.599
PHIL: There is an alternative! There's the little
alleyway!

02:05:49.599 --> 02:05:55.031
ASHLY: No alternative! This is what we're doing.
How many patrons are there? Do I get to know from

02:05:55.031 --> 02:05:56.293
my perception check?

02:05:56.293 --> 02:05:59.562
MATT: Glancing in there, you see probably ten
patrons altogether.

02:05:59.562 --> 02:06:05.125
MARISHA: I look around. Do I see anything that
looks like a children's clothing store? Maybe two

02:06:05.125 --> 02:06:07.976
of us can be a child and three of us can be an
adult.

02:06:07.976 --> 02:06:12.021
IVAN: If each one of us is a leg, and we're three
goblins tall, that's six feet.

02:06:12.021 --> 02:06:14.053
MARISHA: Okay, yeah, no, you're right, Grizz.

02:06:14.053 --> 02:06:18.125
PHIL: Look for a cow costume. Perception check for
a cow costume.

02:06:18.125 --> 02:06:21.726
IVAN: I'll cast Penumbra on you, so at least
you'll be in shadow.

02:06:21.726 --> 02:06:27.151
ASHLY: And then I could stealth. Well, your
stealth is insane, actually. He has +20 stealth.

02:06:27.151 --> 02:06:30.797
TALIESIN: I've got very high stealth, too, so I'm
going to come in with this.

02:06:30.797 --> 02:06:33.992
ASHLY: You guys should go in and get the coat!
I'll go in, too!

02:06:33.992 --> 02:06:36.390
TALIESIN: We're going to sneak in to get the
coat.

02:06:36.390 --> 02:06:38.464
MARISHA: I'll stand guard and watch outside the
window.

02:06:38.464 --> 02:06:40.741
PHIL: I still have my Penumbra, right?

02:06:40.741 --> 02:06:41.793
IVAN: Penumbra.

02:06:41.793 --> 02:06:48.662
MATT: You do not have Penumbra because he cast it
on her, right? Or is it a once at a time thing, or

02:06:48.662 --> 02:06:50.518
can you do multiple people?

02:06:50.518 --> 02:06:52.988
IVAN: That's a good question. Shit. It's in the
Ultimate Magic book.

02:06:52.988 --> 02:06:56.840
MATT: We'll say, for the time being, it affects
both of you. It's fine. Using the shadows around

02:06:56.840 --> 02:07:01.191
you, it's getting late. The angle of the sun,
shadows are not too hard to find. Roll stealth

02:07:01.191 --> 02:07:07.163
checks, all three of you, as you make your way
along the side, darting between barrels and trying

02:07:07.163 --> 02:07:11.794
to find a way into the tavern from the window,
other than the front door.

02:07:11.794 --> 02:07:12.908
ASHLY: 30.

02:07:12.908 --> 02:07:14.156
TALIESIN: 31.

02:07:14.156 --> 02:07:15.241
PHIL: 33.

02:07:15.241 --> 02:07:27.040
MATT: Woo! You guys duck behind every single
possible piece of discarded material, empty crates

02:07:27.040 --> 02:07:32.200
and boxes, barrels that are available. You jump at
certain times, following the lead of Browntooth.

02:07:32.200 --> 02:07:38.449
You manage to find your way through the
thoroughfare to an entrance to the kitchen on the

02:07:38.449 --> 02:07:42.839
side of this tavern. The door is partially ajar.
You look in and there is one person manning the

02:07:42.839 --> 02:07:49.258
kitchen. You see this poor, older woman, who is in
the process of running around with four things

02:07:49.258 --> 02:07:57.671
burning and is like, "There's too many! I hate
festivals! Coming!" She's not paying attention to

02:07:57.671 --> 02:07:59.204
the door right now.

02:07:59.204 --> 02:08:00.617
ASHLY: So we could stealth by her, too?

02:08:00.617 --> 02:08:01.454
MATT: You could try.

02:08:01.454 --> 02:08:03.050
PHIL: Or we could kill her.

02:08:03.050 --> 02:08:07.671
ASHLY: Look, I know I'm a goblin and I love human
blood, but she looks like she's trying her best,

02:08:07.671 --> 02:08:08.944
you know?

02:08:08.944 --> 02:08:13.069
MATT: She seems largely distracted. You guys, with
your current stealth, not an issue. You make your

02:08:13.069 --> 02:08:19.294
way through the kitchen unnoticed. You make your
way into the tavern proper. You can see a handful

02:08:19.294 --> 02:08:23.060
of patrons around a table playing cards, talking to
each other. You hear a couple of them. One

02:08:23.060 --> 02:08:28.636
person's like, "Stupid tradition. I'm just going
to stay here and drink until I care." Takes a big

02:08:28.636 --> 02:08:36.093
old sip. Somebody on the other side of the table
goes, "Speeches every year, speeches! Father

02:08:36.093 --> 02:08:43.495
"Zantas has shown that religion has no sense of
brevity!" You see this other guy at the far end

02:08:43.495 --> 02:08:49.425
table gets up, "And what about you, Zed?" And
slaps the shoulder of the guy who has the large

02:08:49.425 --> 02:08:55.194
coat on. He's leaning forward and goes, "At least
the meals were good. I'm probably going to skip

02:08:55.194 --> 02:09:05.349
"out on the consecration. I've no stomach for
prayer these days." He's face down on the bar

02:09:05.349 --> 02:09:11.379
right there. "Oh, Zed! That'll be me in an hour."
He goes and sits down at the table. There's just

02:09:11.379 --> 02:09:16.138
the barkeep at the bar who's close. Everyone else
is at the table now at the card game and Zed is

02:09:16.138 --> 02:09:18.229
passed out at the bar. What are you going to do?

02:09:18.229 --> 02:09:21.954
ASHLY: Guys, what was the name of that dude we
were supposed to find?

02:09:21.954 --> 02:09:27.121
PHIL: Something with a 'Z,' with two parts. It's
not him.

02:09:27.121 --> 02:09:28.554
ASHLY: It's not him?

02:09:28.554 --> 02:09:29.965
PHIL: He's not wearing blue.

02:09:29.965 --> 02:09:32.984
MATT: No, he's not wearing blue. He's wearing a
dark, muddy brown color.

02:09:32.984 --> 02:09:34.868
ASHLY: Let's steal his coat!

02:09:34.868 --> 02:09:39.328
MATT: All right. The three of you guys going into
this tavern area.

02:09:39.328 --> 02:09:41.269
Go ahead and roll stealth again.

02:09:41.269 --> 02:09:44.835
ASHLY: 20.

02:09:44.835 --> 02:09:48.611
MATT: Cannot roll perception for NPCs today at
all.

02:09:48.611 --> 02:09:49.936
PHIL: 34.

02:09:49.936 --> 02:09:51.033
TALIESIN: 37.

02:09:51.033 --> 02:09:55.794
MATT: You guys dart under one table, wait for a
moment, the barmaid walks by, dart under another

02:09:55.794 --> 02:10:01.456
table. You're chaining your way across this room
between these men. Eventually, finding your way

02:10:01.456 --> 02:10:08.183
right to the outside of this passed-out Zed whose
arm drifts and hangs loosely to his side. His body

02:10:08.183 --> 02:10:13.737
is half against the bar and is a good two minutes
from slumping directly onto the ground

02:10:13.737 --> 02:10:15.250
and off his stool.

02:10:15.250 --> 02:10:16.955
ASHLY: How do we steal it?

02:10:16.955 --> 02:10:18.792
PHIL: Should we wait for him to slump?

02:10:18.792 --> 02:10:25.464
MATT: The barkeep is like, "You okay, Zed?" Pokes
him a little bit.

02:10:25.464 --> 02:10:27.802
TALIESIN: (heavy sigh)

02:10:27.802 --> 02:10:31.523
MATT: "He's all right." Goes back to cleaning a
mug.

02:10:31.523 --> 02:10:39.610
ASHLY: Maybe one of us should distract the barkeep
while the other two grab the coat. Make noise in

02:10:39.610 --> 02:10:41.098
the corner or something.

02:10:41.098 --> 02:10:43.611
IVAN: We're still outside, right?

02:10:43.611 --> 02:10:44.980
MATT: Yeah, you're just waiting.

02:10:44.980 --> 02:10:49.612
IVAN: I keep casting Open and Close on the
outhouse door.

02:10:49.612 --> 02:10:52.443
MATT: (creaking) (slamming)

02:10:52.443 --> 02:10:57.663
TALIESIN: Does Zed have anything on his person
other than a coat?

02:10:57.663 --> 02:11:00.752
MATT: You can only see the coat on him right now
because it's a long trench coat.

02:11:00.752 --> 02:11:02.799
PHIL: We'll throw something to the other side of
the bar.

02:11:02.799 --> 02:11:04.385
ASHLY: Break some glasses. Really distract them.

02:11:04.385 --> 02:11:05.400
MATT: What do you throw?

02:11:05.400 --> 02:11:11.342
TALIESIN: I'm going to grab one of my goblin jag
stars and I'm going to pop one of the bottles on

02:11:11.342 --> 02:11:12.985
the shelf. I assume there's a shelf of bottles.

02:11:12.985 --> 02:11:14.197
MATT: There is a shelf of bottles.

02:11:14.197 --> 02:11:16.433
TALIESIN: I'm going to pop one on the opposite
side of us to try and knock it over.

02:11:16.433 --> 02:11:19.905
MATT: Mezek, you pull out your goblin jag star,
which is essentially the equivalent of a

02:11:19.905 --> 02:11:26.228
shuriken, but it's carved out of pieces of odd,
rusted metal that had been tied together. It's

02:11:26.228 --> 02:11:33.251
more of a cluster of broken whatever you found
from a wagon wheel that was busted weeks ago, but you throw

02:11:33.251 --> 02:11:36.128
it as a ranged weapon. Roll an attack.

02:11:36.128 --> 02:11:40.245
TALIESIN: That's 20.

02:11:40.245 --> 02:11:47.649
MATT: 20. A bottle shatters and sprays across the
back of the barkeep who's like, "Hey, what the

02:11:47.649 --> 02:11:48.766
"hell is that?!"

02:11:48.766 --> 02:11:50.140
TALIESIN: Grab it!

02:11:50.140 --> 02:11:57.025
MATT: He seems currently distracted. The three of
you together make sleight of hand checks right now

02:11:57.025 --> 02:11:59.780
as you rush up to try and pull this off.

02:11:59.780 --> 02:12:01.758
TALIESIN: Where's sleight of hand?

02:12:01.758 --> 02:12:03.747
MATT: This is probably me, sorry.

02:12:03.747 --> 02:12:06.114
IVAN: Should be under sense motive.

02:12:06.114 --> 02:12:07.677
TALIESIN: We don't have it.

02:12:07.677 --> 02:12:08.725
PHIL: I have it.

02:12:08.725 --> 02:12:13.713
MATT: So you guys aren't trained in it, so this
is going to be a basic roll, adding your dexterity

02:12:13.713 --> 02:12:14.828
modifier.

02:12:14.828 --> 02:12:16.747
ASHLY: So 11, then.

02:12:16.747 --> 02:12:18.011
PHIL: 28.

02:12:18.011 --> 02:12:19.093
TALIESIN: 19.

02:12:19.093 --> 02:12:24.033
MATT: Okay, you're all above a ten with two high
rolls, that's good. You all leap up real fast,

02:12:24.033 --> 02:12:28.315
grab his coat, and pull it off of him before
anyone seems to notice.

02:12:28.315 --> 02:12:31.775
TALIESIN: I want to see if he's got anything on
his belt like a pouch or anything like that.

02:12:31.775 --> 02:12:35.276
MATT: You glance, and there is a belt pouch
there.

02:12:35.276 --> 02:12:37.812
TALIESIN: I want to make a stab at grabbing and
ripping it off.

02:12:37.812 --> 02:12:38.961
ASHLY: Don't get greedy!

02:12:38.961 --> 02:12:40.366
MATT: Roll another sleight of hand check.

02:12:40.366 --> 02:12:42.179
IVAN: We're goblins; of course be greedy!

02:12:42.179 --> 02:12:43.322
TALIESIN: What am I rolling?

02:12:43.322 --> 02:12:44.463
MATT: This is another sleight of hand.

02:12:44.463 --> 02:12:45.436
TALIESIN: 15.

02:12:45.436 --> 02:12:50.882
MATT: 15. Okay! You snatch it and all of a sudden
you hear a voice from the front door go, "Hey,

02:12:50.882 --> 02:12:58.246
"what's that? I saw something! Is someone trying to
steal from Zed?!" You hear footsteps as somebody

02:12:58.246 --> 02:13:00.311
begins walking over to where he was right now.

02:13:00.311 --> 02:13:02.651
ASHLY: Go! We run?

02:13:02.651 --> 02:13:05.940
MATT: You guys run? Make stealth checks, guys.

02:13:05.940 --> 02:13:08.618
ASHLY: We have the coat, though, right?

02:13:08.618 --> 02:13:10.176
MATT: You have the coat with you, yeah.

02:13:10.176 --> 02:13:11.680
ASHLY: Oh no!

02:13:11.680 --> 02:13:12.983
PHIL: 40.

02:13:12.983 --> 02:13:14.106
ASHLY: 15.

02:13:14.106 --> 02:13:18.473
TALIESIN: 34.

02:13:18.473 --> 02:13:23.313
MATT: Okay, you guys run. As you're running,
Piglet, you're running behind them hanging on the

02:13:23.313 --> 02:13:27.972
back of the coat and you slam your head at the
bottom of the table, putting a big old knot on it.

02:13:27.972 --> 02:13:33.090
It happens to be the table where the card game was
being played. All the cards go (crashing), all the

02:13:33.090 --> 02:13:38.645
coins scatter in the air. The guys go, "Whoa what
the hell is that?!" And they see as this coat

02:13:38.645 --> 02:13:46.242
scampers off into the kitchen on its own. You guys
hear voices go, "Did you see that?!" "It went in

02:13:46.242 --> 02:13:50.891
"the kitchen, come on!" You hear the sound of
chairs scooting as all of a sudden people are

02:13:50.891 --> 02:13:53.342
beginning to stand up and rush towards the kitchen
after you.

02:13:53.342 --> 02:13:57.472
TALIESIN: While we're running, I'm going to take my
jar of puke and pour it out on the ground behind

02:13:57.472 --> 02:13:59.023
us like a mud slick.

02:13:59.023 --> 02:14:01.115
ASHLY: I have puke, too!

02:14:01.115 --> 02:14:07.809
MATT: You're holding the knot on your head, you
pull the jar, pour it out, and spill this slick

02:14:07.809 --> 02:14:15.242
mass of goblin vomit and whatever else liquid you
put inside there. As you dart through the kitchen,

02:14:15.242 --> 02:14:23.501
the cook goes, "Your food's ready! What the--?!"
And sees you guys dart out the door as the crowd

02:14:23.501 --> 02:14:33.367
comes in and two of them (yell) and fall on their
backs immediately there. A third man steps over

02:14:33.367 --> 02:14:39.056
and follows you into the alleyway. The cook's
like, "You can't be in here! What are you doing?!"

02:14:39.056 --> 02:14:43.607
As the door slams, you guys make your way into the
alley. You see the three of them rush out holding

02:14:43.607 --> 02:14:45.037
the coat.

02:14:45.037 --> 02:14:46.873
MARISHA: What's going on?

02:14:46.873 --> 02:14:50.158
(frantic yelling)

02:14:50.158 --> 02:14:56.878
MARISHA: I'm so glad I planned for this. And I go,
go guys. Smoke bomb!

02:14:56.878 --> 02:15:05.897
MATT: As the door opens again, you see this
breastplate-adorned guard of the city who is

02:15:05.897 --> 02:15:11.979
essentially the bouncer of this place, rushes out,
blade drawn, helmet half-cocked on his face where

02:15:11.979 --> 02:15:17.609
it doesn't fit right and one eye looks higher than
the other, and he goes, "You!" (explosion) As

02:15:17.609 --> 02:15:21.497
smoke fills this entire alleyway, he begins
coughing.

02:15:21.497 --> 02:15:25.759
MARISHA: Before the cloud gets too thick, I go--
and run.

02:15:25.759 --> 02:15:29.326
ASHLY: We should go in the outhouse and assemble
our Mary Kate and Ashley situation.

02:15:29.326 --> 02:15:30.541
MARISHA: Okay, let's do it!

02:15:30.541 --> 02:15:33.017
IVAN: We should probably not do it in the
outhouse.

02:15:33.017 --> 02:15:36.880
TALIESIN: We can run all the way around the
alleyway from this. Let's get down the alley.

02:15:36.880 --> 02:15:41.692
MATT: You guys rush out of the alleyway, you get
out of the fog, you manage to dart off to the side

02:15:41.692 --> 02:15:46.394
and wait a little bit. You hear that guard wander
off and start shouting, and vanishes in the

02:15:46.394 --> 02:15:49.432
distance. After a few moments of waiting, you're
pretty certain he hasn't been able to keep up with

02:15:49.432 --> 02:15:52.883
your trail because you're &lt;i&gt;that stealthy.&lt;/i&gt; Are you
going to do this?

02:15:52.883 --> 02:15:54.465
ASHLY: Yeah! Who wants to be the head?

02:15:54.465 --> 02:15:55.926
IVAN: That's the important one.

02:15:55.926 --> 02:15:58.671
PHIL: We all have goblin heads.

02:15:58.671 --> 02:16:01.478
IVAN: I have a 17 charisma.

02:16:01.478 --> 02:16:03.483
MARISHA: I don't like talking to people.

02:16:03.483 --> 02:16:06.187
ASHLY: Whoever has the highest charisma should
definitely be the head.

02:16:06.187 --> 02:16:08.177
IVAN: Grizznak the Great will be the head!

02:16:08.177 --> 02:16:11.490
MATT: This is the best goblin Voltron ever!

02:16:11.490 --> 02:16:18.605
IVAN: Hello, fellow human! Aren't you having a
wonderful human day today?

02:16:18.605 --> 02:16:21.161
PHIL: You guys have the high strength.

02:16:21.161 --> 02:16:26.297
TALIESIN: Well, we've got the high dex. You should
be the middle, so we'll be the legs.

02:16:26.297 --> 02:16:32.295
IVAN: You form the torso. I will form the head and
together we shall be Goblon!

02:16:32.295 --> 02:16:35.992
MARISHA: I've been doing a lot of crunches, so I
feel pretty good about being the core.

02:16:35.992 --> 02:16:37.342
TALIESIN: What's in the pouch?

02:16:37.342 --> 02:16:41.769
MATT: In the pouch you find eight gold pieces, a
small snuff box.

02:16:41.769 --> 02:16:44.929
TALIESIN: Ooh! I eat all the snuff.

02:16:44.929 --> 02:16:45.980
MATT: Okay!

02:16:45.980 --> 02:16:47.733
PHIL: You're flying!

02:16:47.733 --> 02:16:51.412
MARISHA: What did you eat?!

02:16:51.412 --> 02:16:54.766
MATT: Roll a will saving throw.

02:16:54.766 --> 02:17:00.483
TALIESIN: Where's my will saving throw? There it
is. 16.

02:17:00.483 --> 02:17:06.473
MATT: 16. Okay. The world gets a little funny for
a bit, and you feel exhilarated, though a little

02:17:06.473 --> 02:17:14.761
unfocused. What normally is the goblin ADHD is now
in hyperdrive. You're looking everywhere. We have

02:17:14.761 --> 02:17:16.516
Grizznak as the head.

02:17:16.516 --> 02:17:17.754
IVAN: Grizznak forms the head!

02:17:17.754 --> 02:17:18.946
PHIL: We are the middle.

02:17:18.946 --> 02:17:20.011
MATT: You guys are the middle.

02:17:20.011 --> 02:17:21.239
MARISHA and TALIESIN: We're the legs.

02:17:21.239 --> 02:17:25.492
MATT: With that, you stand up, coat goes on,
snapping it shut.

02:17:25.492 --> 02:17:28.634
ASHLY: I give Grizznak my pretty hat.

02:17:28.634 --> 02:17:35.277
IVAN: Okay. I actually have a goblin's wizard's
hat.

02:17:35.277 --> 02:17:38.443
ASHLY: Can you put it on top to humor me?

02:17:38.443 --> 02:17:43.376
IVAN: Why don't you put it under one of our arms
so it looks like we're carrying a helmet?

02:17:43.376 --> 02:17:45.248
ASHLY: All right. Fair enough.

02:17:45.248 --> 02:17:47.979
IVAN: I'll probably get away more with the wizard
hat.

02:17:47.979 --> 02:17:49.767
PHIL: Oh, you think?

02:17:49.767 --> 02:17:52.861
MATT: So, where are you guys going?

02:17:52.861 --> 02:17:58.652
PHIL: We're going towards where the people were
going. Was the alleyway

02:17:58.652 --> 02:18:00.402
parallel to the main street?

02:18:00.402 --> 02:18:02.299
MATT: It was, yeah. You follow that.

02:18:02.299 --> 02:18:03.578
PHIL: Head down the alleyway.

02:18:03.578 --> 02:18:06.119
MATT: Great. The sky has cleared, by the way.

02:18:06.119 --> 02:18:07.487
PHIL: Like Vincent D'onofrio.

02:18:07.487 --> 02:18:09.533
MARISHA: Yes, like Men in Black.

02:18:09.533 --> 02:18:17.512
MATT: Okay, so! (laughs) I'm so happy right now.

02:18:17.512 --> 02:18:20.231
IVAN: Hello!

02:18:20.231 --> 02:18:21.748
PHIL: Morning!

02:18:21.748 --> 02:18:28.738
MATT: As you guys trudge down the alleyway, the
sky is clear now. Most of the upper areas are dry

02:18:28.738 --> 02:18:32.195
other than a few rain barrels that have caught a
lot of water in the side of this alleyway. You can

02:18:32.195 --> 02:18:40.040
hear the music in the distance, you can hear the
laughter of children, you can hear people playing.

02:18:40.040 --> 02:18:46.419
It sounds like this festival is in heavy swing.
You come to the end of the alleyway into an open

02:18:46.419 --> 02:18:54.623
town square, a main open thoroughfare with large
tents that are erected, with large carts, people

02:18:54.623 --> 02:19:01.313
barking for food, different carnival games set up
throughout this area. What you notice amongst the

02:19:01.313 --> 02:19:10.426
buildings and houses is a large stone cathedral
that looms over this entire area. In front of this

02:19:10.426 --> 02:19:19.108
cathedral, there is a raised platform where the band
is playing, where the music's coming from. People

02:19:19.108 --> 02:19:26.374
all around this area are now talking and families
laughing. There are small poles that are erected

02:19:26.374 --> 02:19:29.209
that are covered in flower wreaths that are hung
around it.

02:19:29.209 --> 02:19:31.197
PHIL: Sounds gay.

02:19:31.197 --> 02:19:35.217
MATT: Actually, quite happy and jovial.

02:19:35.217 --> 02:19:44.140
IVAN: Never been so disgusted in my entire life. I
poke my legs and my torso to move them forward so

02:19:44.140 --> 02:19:48.976
that we can get closer to the stone. Does it look
like there's a speech

02:19:48.976 --> 02:19:50.525
that's going to be starting soon?

02:19:50.525 --> 02:19:52.628
MATT: People are gathered towards the center of
this area around that.

02:19:52.628 --> 02:20:01.233
IVAN: I would like to motion my torso and my legs
to be on the outer edge of the front couple of

02:20:01.233 --> 02:20:03.055
lines of the group.

02:20:03.055 --> 02:20:04.070
MATT: Okay.

02:20:04.070 --> 02:20:06.296
PHIL: Look and see if there's anybody wearing
blue.

02:20:06.296 --> 02:20:08.254
ASHLY: Yeah, look for the blue poop.

02:20:08.254 --> 02:20:14.595
IVAN: Blue. I see silver. I see brown, which is
nice. I see red. I see--

02:20:14.595 --> 02:20:16.173
ASHLY: What about blue? I don't care about the
other colors!

02:20:16.173 --> 02:20:17.775
IVAN: I see purple. You mean yellow?

02:20:17.775 --> 02:20:18.991
ASHLY: No! Blue!

02:20:18.991 --> 02:20:20.672
PHIL: Look for the guy in the blue!

02:20:20.672 --> 02:20:22.336
IVAN: I see a blue sky!

02:20:22.336 --> 02:20:29.035
MATT: As this is happening, a drunk man,
30-something, a red chin-strap beard, and long

02:20:29.035 --> 02:20:36.010
hair pulled into a top knot has a tankard in front
of him and, (hiccup) "Hey, happy Autumn's-thing."

02:20:36.010 --> 02:20:39.286
IVAN: Happy Autumn's-thing!

02:20:39.286 --> 02:20:41.004
MATT: Make a bluff check.

02:20:41.004 --> 02:20:44.934
IVAN: Oh, I'm so good at bluff. 15.

02:20:44.934 --> 02:20:49.681
MATT: He goes, "I think you need some more of this
than I do."

02:20:49.681 --> 02:20:52.216
IVAN: Yeah, I do!

02:20:52.216 --> 02:20:54.316
MATT: He pats you on the back with a hefty arm.

02:20:54.316 --> 02:20:56.874
MARISHA: Whoa!

02:20:56.874 --> 02:21:02.600
MATT: Since you are the guys that are holding the
legs right now, I need you to both

02:21:02.600 --> 02:21:04.015
make strength checks.

02:21:04.015 --> 02:21:05.486
TALIESIN: Oh god!

02:21:05.486 --> 02:21:06.722
ASHLY: 20.

02:21:06.722 --> 02:21:08.100
TALIESIN: Five.

02:21:08.100 --> 02:21:13.647
MATT: Five. One leg, whoa, goes forward, and you
stumble and take a knee like you're kneeling in

02:21:13.647 --> 02:21:16.603
the middle of the street. And the man who holds
the drink goes--

02:21:16.603 --> 02:21:18.577
ASHLY: Kids, I want to talk to you about safe sex.

02:21:18.577 --> 02:21:26.819
IVAN: I am reflecting upon the glory that is this
most holy day--

02:21:26.819 --> 02:21:28.483
PHIL: Stop talking!

02:21:28.483 --> 02:21:34.434
MATT: "Oh, you're one of them church types. Never
mind." And the guy stumbles off. At this point,

02:21:34.434 --> 02:21:36.862
you see the crowd starting to hush a little and
gather towards--

02:21:36.862 --> 02:21:38.780
TALIESIN: Hup!

02:21:38.780 --> 02:21:42.577
MATT: You get back up. Make a perception check if
you could, Grizznak.

02:21:42.577 --> 02:21:46.627
IVAN: Okay, that was very close. 17.

02:21:46.627 --> 02:21:49.427
MATT: 17. Glancing up, you can see now--

02:21:49.427 --> 02:21:54.163
IVAN: I try not to put my little hand up. I put it
back down.

02:21:54.163 --> 02:22:01.085
MATT: The people that are gathering towards this
central platform area you can see a person

02:22:01.085 --> 02:22:06.386
ascending the steps on the side. What you see is a
man dressed in simple, but elegant blue robes that

02:22:06.386 --> 02:22:10.906
walks from the cathedral, who is standing now at a
podium in the center of this. As people begin to

02:22:10.906 --> 02:22:18.377
hush, some yell towards him. He has short brown
hair and a well-kept beard that show a social

02:22:18.377 --> 02:22:24.379
station amongst the townspeople, although his
demeanor is very humble. But some people are

02:22:24.379 --> 02:22:28.115
paying attention to him, some people are looking
around, some people are still yelling and playing

02:22:28.115 --> 02:22:30.787
games. He seems to be a little frustrated that no
one's paying attention.

02:22:30.787 --> 02:22:33.672
IVAN: Blue alert! Blue alert! We have a code blue!

02:22:33.672 --> 02:22:34.873
TALIESIN: Running towards it.

02:22:34.873 --> 02:22:37.286
PHIL: Does he have a stone?

02:22:37.286 --> 02:22:38.818
IVAN: Can I see the stone at all?

02:22:38.818 --> 02:22:43.274
MATT: You do not see a stone. However, as you guys
begin to make your way through the crowd, and

02:22:43.274 --> 02:22:46.840
everyone's paying attention to various things in
the area, he reaches into the pocket of his robe

02:22:46.840 --> 02:22:57.480
and pulls out a small cast iron pellet about that
large. And he takes it, looks around, and throws

02:22:57.480 --> 02:23:06.695
it to the top of this platform. As it hits the
woodwork, you hear a sudden (thunderclap). It

02:23:06.695 --> 02:23:11.152
causes this echo of thunder throughout the
entirety of this area and everyone stops and goes

02:23:11.152 --> 02:23:12.245
(gasp).

02:23:12.245 --> 02:23:13.445
IVAN: He's got a boom cube.

02:23:13.445 --> 02:23:14.593
MARISHA: He's got a boom-boom rock.

02:23:14.593 --> 02:23:16.657
ASHLY: Is that the rock we want?

02:23:16.657 --> 02:23:18.230
IVAN: No, it's not the rock, but I like that rock.

02:23:18.230 --> 02:23:19.459
PHIL: That's the rock we want!

02:23:19.459 --> 02:23:24.159
IVAN: No, it's not, it's just a boom-boom rock.
Guys! You've seen boom-boom rocks. We all know

02:23:24.159 --> 02:23:25.387
about boom-boom rocks.

02:23:25.387 --> 02:23:26.700
PHIL: Have we seen these before?

02:23:26.700 --> 02:23:28.033
MATT: You have not.

02:23:28.033 --> 02:23:33.650
IVAN: Okay, well, Grizznak likes to &lt;i&gt;think&lt;/i&gt; he's
seen a boom-boom rock before because he's the

02:23:33.650 --> 02:23:36.050
smartest and the greatest Grizznak.

02:23:36.050 --> 02:23:38.512
ASHLY: Is there a way to confirm whether or not
that's the rock that--?

02:23:38.512 --> 02:23:42.780
MATT: Actually, for you, go ahead and roll a
wisdom check.

02:23:42.780 --> 02:23:44.523
IVAN: Oh, hohohoho.

02:23:44.523 --> 02:23:46.427
PHIL: O Grizznak the Barely Alive.

02:23:46.427 --> 02:23:48.395
IVAN: 21.

02:23:48.395 --> 02:23:51.807
MATT: You realize at this moment, as you were
instructing the goblins that can't possibly

02:23:51.807 --> 02:23:59.316
be the stone because that's a boom-boom rock, you
realize, holy shit, this entire journey was to

02:23:59.316 --> 02:24:01.108
retrieve a boom-boom rock.

02:24:01.108 --> 02:24:10.155
IVAN: Guys, Guffeye wants us to get boom-boom
rocks.

02:24:10.155 --> 02:24:13.315
ASHLY: Why does she want us to get boom-boom
rocks?

02:24:13.315 --> 02:24:15.046
IVAN: Because they're boom-boom rocks!

02:24:15.046 --> 02:24:17.211
ASHLY: But we have boom-boom rocks back home!

02:24:17.211 --> 02:24:22.030
MATT: With this, suddenly, you hear screams. You
hear dogs starting to bark in the distance and you

02:24:22.030 --> 02:24:26.972
see the glow of flames over across the way as two
streets, three streets away, you see fire

02:24:26.972 --> 02:24:29.227
beginning to glow and plumes of smoke build up.

02:24:29.227 --> 02:24:30.344
MARISHA: Fire!

02:24:30.344 --> 02:24:33.784
MATT: People begin to run, and chaos breaks in the
crowd as people begin looking about, screaming,

02:24:33.784 --> 02:24:36.800
"What's going on?! We're under attack! Goblins are
here!"

02:24:36.800 --> 02:24:45.955
IVAN: Okay, so Goblon is going to lurch forward,
and I'm going to try and see-- does he have like a

02:24:45.955 --> 02:24:48.283
pouch of boom-boom rocks? Or anything like that?

02:24:48.283 --> 02:24:53.358
MATT: No, all you see is the single stone rolling
off the top of the stage--

02:24:53.358 --> 02:24:54.607
IVAN: Mage Hand.

02:24:54.607 --> 02:24:59.017
MATT: Okay, you Mage Hand and the stone stops
there in place as you begin walking towards it.

02:24:59.017 --> 02:25:04.441
The crowd now is scattering and running away as
people are trying to flee from this distant flame.

02:25:04.441 --> 02:25:10.001
You hear another explosion in the distance as a
section of burning wood flips.

02:25:10.001 --> 02:25:15.774
MARISHA: Someone's making really &lt;i&gt;big&lt;/i&gt; boom-booms.
I want to meet &lt;i&gt;that&lt;/i&gt; person!

02:25:15.774 --> 02:25:19.265
PHIL: Do you think that had anything to do with
the fire you set?

02:25:19.265 --> 02:25:21.883
IVAN: I don't think it's the fire that I set in
the tavern.

02:25:21.883 --> 02:25:25.805
ASHLY: Wait, guys, remember? There's other goblins
here.

02:25:25.805 --> 02:25:28.682
IVAN: Remember, it's the Seven-Teeth--

02:25:28.682 --> 02:25:30.205
PHIL: We've got to get the rock!

02:25:30.205 --> 02:25:32.057
TALIESIN: Too many tooth! Get the rock.

02:25:32.057 --> 02:25:35.288
PHIL: Wait, I'll ask you. Is anyone watching us?

02:25:35.288 --> 02:25:40.017
IVAN: I think everyone's pretty distracted by the
big boom-booms.

02:25:40.017 --> 02:25:44.638
MARISHA: Here, I can help clear this area out,
too. I light another little firecracker and throw

02:25:44.638 --> 02:25:47.562
it down next to us to scare the crowd.

02:25:47.562 --> 02:25:51.446
MATT: Okay, so as you throw another firecracker,
you guys stumble forward, foot by foot. I want you

02:25:51.446 --> 02:25:57.184
to make another bluff check. And I want both the
legs, both of you guys to make another strength

02:25:57.184 --> 02:25:58.937
check to try and get there quickly.

02:25:58.937 --> 02:26:01.614
IVAN: Natural 20. That puts me up to 27.

02:26:01.614 --> 02:26:02.734
MATT: Okay.

02:26:02.734 --> 02:26:04.411
ASHLY: Nine.

02:26:04.411 --> 02:26:05.414
TALIESIN: Ten.

02:26:05.414 --> 02:26:11.469
MATT: Okay, so: as you're rushing forward you can
see the crowd look at you as you turn and be like,

02:26:11.469 --> 02:26:16.174
"No! Don't go that way! The goblins are that way!"
And they're actually genuinely trying to save you.

02:26:16.174 --> 02:26:19.019
IVAN: I will save us from this goblin scum!

02:26:19.019 --> 02:26:23.954
MATT: And as you say that, the firecracker goes
off behind. Everyone looks around distracted, as

02:26:23.954 --> 02:26:31.899
both of your legs tumble forward and you tumble
forward. The coat unravels as what was once a

02:26:31.899 --> 02:26:36.129
single entity rolls into five goblin balls that
all (rolling thumps) across the stonework,

02:26:36.129 --> 02:26:43.237
slamming into the base of this platform. You guys
can hear the distant screams of goblins two or

02:26:43.237 --> 02:26:46.022
three streets over where the main battle's
happening. The guards have moved in that

02:26:46.022 --> 02:26:53.347
direction. This open thoroughfare is mostly empty
of all people at this time. You glance over and

02:26:53.347 --> 02:26:58.395
can see the stone is in the center of a light
piece of mud that hasn't fully dried from the

02:26:58.395 --> 02:26:59.303
earlier storm.

02:26:59.303 --> 02:27:00.441
PHIL: I go to get the stone.

02:27:00.441 --> 02:27:07.022
MATT: You rush forward, grab the stone, and put it
in your hand. You hear a voice say, "Halt! You

02:27:07.022 --> 02:27:13.235
"will walk no further, foul creature! Sarenrae's
vengeance will end your existence." You all glance

02:27:13.235 --> 02:27:17.680
over to the left of you and you see a woman
dressed in gold armor and light blue cloth

02:27:17.680 --> 02:27:22.660
clutching a scimitar in one hand and a small gold
statue of a winged woman in the other. As she

02:27:22.660 --> 02:27:27.138
glares at you, you hear a voice behind her say,
"Come on, Kyra, don't think we'll let you

02:27:27.138 --> 02:27:32.550
"have all the fun to yourself." You see, walking up
behind her, a small halfling man grinning with

02:27:32.550 --> 02:27:39.348
shaggy blond hair saunters up, pulling out a
flute. Behind him, a human in heavy armor, his

02:27:39.348 --> 02:27:45.855
long brown, unkempt hair around his shoulders
draws two blades and scowls. "Goblins, of course."

02:27:45.855 --> 02:27:53.043
He readies himself as a shield appears before him
as another heavily armored figure steps in front

02:27:53.043 --> 02:27:58.133
of the lot. A tall woman wielding a longsword, her
hair pulled back tight and her face tense goes,

02:27:58.133 --> 02:28:04.263
"Behind me. We shall smite them where they stand."
Behind all of them, you see an older man with long

02:28:04.263 --> 02:28:09.985
white hair and a beard hold up a staff and smirk.
"Well, Seelah, I can just destroy them from here.

02:28:09.985 --> 02:28:13.520
"That's fine with me." I need you all to roll
initiative.

02:28:13.520 --> 02:28:14.698
TALIESIN: Oh, shit.

02:28:14.698 --> 02:28:16.130
IVAN: Adventuring party.

02:28:16.130 --> 02:28:17.919
MARISHA: Damn adventuring parties.

02:28:17.919 --> 02:28:20.617
ASHLY: 21.

02:28:20.617 --> 02:28:21.893
MARISHA: 22.

02:28:21.893 --> 02:28:23.681
IVAN: Look at all this adventure.

02:28:23.681 --> 02:28:25.251
TALIESIN: Five.

02:28:25.251 --> 02:28:26.419
IVAN: I'm at an eight.

02:28:26.419 --> 02:28:27.519
PHIL: 24.

02:28:27.519 --> 02:28:29.302
MATT: All right, hold on just a second.

02:28:29.302 --> 02:28:31.341
ASHLY: There's no fleeing in D&amp;amp;D is there?

02:28:31.341 --> 02:28:33.086
MARISHA: Yeah, you can flee.

02:28:33.086 --> 02:28:34.449
PHIL: Oh, watch!

02:28:34.449 --> 02:28:37.607
TALIESIN: You can do anything you like.

02:28:37.607 --> 02:28:39.758
IVAN: If you've never seen goblins run before--

02:28:39.758 --> 02:28:42.534
PHIL: You're going to see some hellacious fleeing
right now.

02:28:42.534 --> 02:28:43.851
MARISHA: I'm not above it.

02:28:43.851 --> 02:28:54.564
PHIL: Because there's a lot of them with armor and
winged statuary!

02:28:54.564 --> 02:29:00.881
MARISHA: They got lots of hair. We've got really
big ears, though.

02:29:00.881 --> 02:29:04.519
MATT: 20? Higher than 20, anybody?

02:29:04.519 --> 02:29:05.659
PHIL: 24.

02:29:05.659 --> 02:29:06.673
ASHLY: 21.

02:29:06.673 --> 02:29:07.520
MARISHA: 22.

02:29:07.520 --> 02:29:09.528
MATT: Damn, look at that! All right.

02:29:09.528 --> 02:29:14.475
IVAN: Super runaway!

02:29:14.475 --> 02:29:18.847
MATT: That's Browntooth. You had--

02:29:18.847 --> 02:29:20.230
ASHLY: 21.

02:29:20.230 --> 02:29:21.282
MARISHA: 22.

02:29:21.282 --> 02:29:23.110
TALIESIN: We've got the rock?

02:29:23.110 --> 02:29:24.281
PHIL: I've got the rock.

02:29:24.281 --> 02:29:27.415
IVAN: Glad that we were able to keep it.

02:29:27.415 --> 02:29:29.708
PHIL: So far.

02:29:29.708 --> 02:29:36.325
MATT: These humans look ready and eager, and
there's a part of you that's like, "Oh man, it

02:29:36.325 --> 02:29:39.304
"would feel good to cut them down." It is up to you
what you want to do.

02:29:39.304 --> 02:29:41.966
PHIL: How many of them are there?

02:29:41.966 --> 02:29:43.081
TALIESIN: Four.

02:29:43.081 --> 02:29:46.442
IVAN: Four against five. Those are good goblin
numbers.

02:29:46.442 --> 02:29:47.745
ASHLY: There's five of them.

02:29:47.745 --> 02:29:54.395
IVAN: Oh, there's five of them? There's five of
us. That's bad goblin numbers. That's very bad

02:29:54.395 --> 02:29:55.789
goblin numbers.

02:29:55.789 --> 02:30:01.924
MATT: 20 to 15, anybody?

02:30:01.924 --> 02:30:03.837
IVAN: Ten to 15?

02:30:03.837 --> 02:30:06.470
MATT: Sorry, 20 to 15. Nope? All right.

02:30:06.470 --> 02:30:14.810
ASHLY: I'm all for smashing stuff, but I smashed a
wall, I smashed a crate. I'm down to run.

02:30:14.810 --> 02:30:16.349
MATT: 15 to ten?

02:30:16.349 --> 02:30:19.121
IVAN: 15 to ten, no.

02:30:19.121 --> 02:30:22.746
MATT: Nope. Ten to five?

02:30:22.746 --> 02:30:23.949
IVAN: Eight.

02:30:23.949 --> 02:30:25.269
TALIESIN: Five.

02:30:25.269 --> 02:30:33.028
TALIESIN: I like the random sounds of sheep being
tortured.

02:30:33.028 --> 02:30:35.829
MARISHA: (sheep bleating)

02:30:35.829 --> 02:30:39.041
TALIESIN: Thursday night. It's a nice Sunday night
right there.

02:30:39.041 --> 02:30:46.455
MATT: Top of the round. All of them charge into
the square as the rest scattered. Bring this in

02:30:46.455 --> 02:30:51.451
here. Browntooth, you're up first.

02:30:51.451 --> 02:30:58.814
PHIL: I look for some place to hide and head there
as quickly as possible.

02:30:58.814 --> 02:31:05.533
MATT: Closest place to hide here would be behind this
cart or behind the platform.

02:31:05.533 --> 02:31:08.715
PHIL: Where are the attacking people?

02:31:08.715 --> 02:31:10.435
MATT: They're right here.

02:31:10.435 --> 02:31:20.094
PHIL: Ah! There they are. I get behind the
platform.

02:31:20.094 --> 02:31:28.073
MATT: You duck around here. Go ahead and roll a
stealth check to hide in the shadows.

02:31:28.073 --> 02:31:31.514
PHIL: 30.

02:31:31.514 --> 02:31:33.354
MATT: 13?

02:31:33.354 --> 02:31:34.496
PHIL: 30.

02:31:34.496 --> 02:31:38.177
MATT: 30! Okay! You duck underneath the platform,
keeping an eye on what's happening.

02:31:38.177 --> 02:31:39.757
Is that your turn?

02:31:39.757 --> 02:31:40.846
PHIL: Can I see them?

02:31:40.846 --> 02:31:41.830
MATT: You can see them.

02:31:41.830 --> 02:31:45.356
PHIL: Yes, that's my turn.

02:31:45.356 --> 02:31:47.522
MATT: Snizzler, it's your turn.

02:31:47.522 --> 02:31:55.478
MARISHA: First, I'm going to take a pipe bomb and
throw it right at that one.

02:31:55.478 --> 02:32:01.995
MATT: Right there? All right. He is 25 feet away.
Do you want to get a little closer to do it?

02:32:01.995 --> 02:32:05.835
MARISHA: I move up one square and then I hit him.

02:32:05.835 --> 02:32:08.330
MATT: Lob it! Roll for an attack.

02:32:08.330 --> 02:32:12.104
IVAN: Goblin pipe bombs!

02:32:12.104 --> 02:32:13.351
MARISHA: 18!

02:32:13.351 --> 02:32:14.888
MATT: 18 hits!

02:32:14.888 --> 02:32:16.398
ASHLY: Nice!

02:32:16.398 --> 02:32:19.012
MATT: It is a touch attack, correct?

02:32:19.012 --> 02:32:20.328
MARISHA: Touch attack.

02:32:20.328 --> 02:32:23.343
MATT: He's actually on fire right now.

02:32:23.343 --> 02:32:28.447
MARISHA: Everyone in a ten foot radius must make a
reflex save.

02:32:28.447 --> 02:32:30.439
MATT: Indeed. What's the DC on that?

02:32:30.439 --> 02:32:32.036
MARISHA: 14.

02:32:32.036 --> 02:32:47.927
MATT: That is a failure, success, success. Three
damage, three damage, and six damage. Nice!

02:32:47.927 --> 02:32:56.832
MARISHA: Plus the main dude takes 13 damage.

02:32:56.832 --> 02:33:00.447
MATT: 13 points of damage! Woo!

02:33:00.447 --> 02:33:06.661
MARISHA: Can I use the rest of my movement to also
run backwards?

02:33:06.661 --> 02:33:10.277
MATT: Sure.

02:33:10.277 --> 02:33:13.041
MARISHA: Run towards these things.

02:33:13.041 --> 02:33:15.681
MATT: That's about as far as you can get right
there.

02:33:15.681 --> 02:33:16.954
MARISHA: That's fine.

02:33:16.954 --> 02:33:23.212
MATT: You run up, fling it, and dart away, as it
lands at the foot of the guy with the blades out,

02:33:23.212 --> 02:33:28.376
he prepares himself and goes to guard as it
(explosion) bursts in front of him. You can see

02:33:28.376 --> 02:33:32.753
the flames coast up and now the fire is caught
into his hair and his armor is burning from

02:33:32.753 --> 02:33:38.507
whatever goblin liquid, napalm-like material you
had in there adhered to him. As the fire bursts

02:33:38.507 --> 02:33:42.488
outward in a ten foot radius because of your
goblin expertise with explosive devices, the

02:33:42.488 --> 02:33:48.327
flames catch the three other allies of his, who
all manage to avoid most of the impact. But you

02:33:48.327 --> 02:33:52.823
do see them scarred and burned a little bit from
the side of the blast. The fighter is furious as

02:33:52.823 --> 02:33:55.943
the flames lick across his torso. That ends your
turn. Piglet, you're up.

02:33:55.943 --> 02:34:03.245
ASHLY: Well, you lit them on fire, so now I want
to smash them. But maybe I should run away.

02:34:03.245 --> 02:34:04.764
TALIESIN: Follow your heart.

02:34:04.764 --> 02:34:07.017
PHIL: Ranged attack? No.

02:34:07.017 --> 02:34:08.412
ASHLY: I don't have a ranged attack.

