damage multiplier on that?

02:50:34.779 --> 02:50:35.683
ASHLY: Huh?

02:50:35.683 --> 02:50:37.291
MATT: It should have a multiplier next to the
weapon.

02:50:37.291 --> 02:50:38.523
ASHLY: Times three.

02:50:38.523 --> 02:50:40.313
MATT: Roll 3d10.

02:50:40.313 --> 02:50:42.100
ASHLY: 3d10?!

02:50:42.100 --> 02:50:49.495
MATT: Yes, plus six. 3d10 plus six damage.

02:50:49.495 --> 02:50:53.122
PHIL: Are the zeroes tens?

02:50:53.122 --> 02:50:54.151
MATT: Yeah.

02:50:54.151 --> 02:50:58.743
ASHLY: Oh, zeroes are tens? 21 plus six. 26.

02:50:58.743 --> 02:51:03.405
MATT: How do you want to finish him off? Because
you destroy him. So, the man who's on fire in

02:51:03.405 --> 02:51:04.947
front of you with his two weapons out.

02:51:04.947 --> 02:51:06.363
PHIL: That's the one you hit?

02:51:06.363 --> 02:51:08.657
ASHLY: That's the guy. Damn it, I wish I had gone
for the other one.

02:51:08.657 --> 02:51:13.420
MATT: How do you want to finish him off? He's
(heavy breathing).

02:51:13.420 --> 02:51:20.767
ASHLY: I want to knock his head off with the
hammer and I want it to fall into the lap of his

02:51:20.767 --> 02:51:26.340
now grieving friend and spray blood all over them.
The most adjacent friend. No, the bard.

02:51:26.340 --> 02:51:27.167
I hate the bard.

02:51:27.167 --> 02:51:28.347
MATT: The bard?

02:51:28.347 --> 02:51:30.225
ASHLY: Hit the bard in the head with his friend's
head.

02:51:30.225 --> 02:51:36.795
MATT: You swing as the fighter goes to parry your
blow. Your goblin rage gets you a faster speed

02:51:36.795 --> 02:51:41.044
than he ever expected. As he goes to swing it to
the side, the hammer comes straight across from

02:51:41.044 --> 02:51:44.434
the direction he wasn't expecting, like an
unintentional feint. His eyes goes wide for a

02:51:44.434 --> 02:51:49.693
second before the hammer (slams) and the head gets
carried off of his shoulders. It spins backwards,

02:51:49.693 --> 02:51:56.039
and the bard, who's singing his song, looks up as
his friend's head towards him. Falls onto his feet and goes

02:51:56.039 --> 02:52:02.567
(yells). Makes a concentration. Fails his
concentration. I'll say the song ends, he has to

02:52:02.567 --> 02:52:10.569
start it again because he just saw his friend's
head land at his feet. He goes, "Valero? You!" You

02:52:10.569 --> 02:52:14.528
can see there is a genuine horror and sadness in
his face.

02:52:14.528 --> 02:52:16.100
ASHLY: I go: Yay!

02:52:16.100 --> 02:52:18.859
TALIESIN: You still have a bite attack!

02:52:18.859 --> 02:52:20.136
ASHLY: I still have a bite attack!

02:52:20.136 --> 02:52:21.198
MATT: Yes, you do!

02:52:21.198 --> 02:52:22.459
ASHLY: Who's by him?

02:52:22.459 --> 02:52:24.797
MATT: This is the paladin right here.

02:52:24.797 --> 02:52:25.948
ASHLY: I'll bite the paladin.

02:52:25.948 --> 02:52:28.693
MATT: Go for it. Roll for attack.

02:52:28.693 --> 02:52:30.382
TALIESIN: Cleric's right there.

02:52:30.382 --> 02:52:31.951
ASHLY: Is that a six or a nine?

02:52:31.951 --> 02:52:34.368
TALIESIN: That's a nine.

02:52:34.368 --> 02:52:36.896
ASHLY: That's a nine? Okay, so 13?

02:52:36.896 --> 02:52:43.381
MATT: 13? Oh, the paladin? Yeah, it definitely
misses the paladin. Her shield's too big. You go

02:52:43.381 --> 02:52:47.876
to bite her and she slams the shield out and you
catch metal instead. She pulls the shield away and

02:52:47.876 --> 02:52:52.431
you scrape tooth marks against the metal, which is
impressive for a goblin. She looks at you and

02:52:52.431 --> 02:52:58.418
goes, "You! You foul, terrible creature! You will
pay for what you've done!" You see tears in her

02:52:58.418 --> 02:53:00.841
eyes. That ends your turn?

02:53:00.841 --> 02:53:10.045
ASHLY: I go: Heh, loser. I'm going to stay there.
Maybe that's unwise, but I'm

02:53:10.045 --> 02:53:11.604
just going to stay there.

02:53:11.604 --> 02:53:19.708
MATT: The bard is too angry to even consider-- no.
No, he's too angry. He's not going to be able to

02:53:19.708 --> 02:53:24.010
do his bard performances this turn. He's too
fraught with frustration.

02:53:24.010 --> 02:53:26.664
He's going to cast Sleep.

02:53:26.664 --> 02:53:28.219
MARISHA: Oh, shit.

02:53:28.219 --> 02:53:36.967
MATT: As part of the Sleep spell, just to double
check what the saves are; I believe it's a will

02:53:36.967 --> 02:53:57.163
save. There we go, we got Sleep. Give me a second,
guys. I need you to make a will saving throw.

02:53:57.163 --> 02:53:59.635
ASHLY: A will saving throw? Okay.

02:53:59.635 --> 02:54:01.725
MATT: You get plus two because you're raging.

02:54:01.725 --> 02:54:04.141
ASHLY: Where is my--?

02:54:04.141 --> 02:54:08.455
TALIESIN: It's on the third square on the right.

02:54:08.455 --> 02:54:17.561
ASHLY: Oh, I see. Okay. 19.

02:54:17.561 --> 02:54:23.480
MATT: With that, you look over as the bard ends up
singing this incantation in a language you don't

02:54:23.480 --> 02:54:29.902
understand. You feel a wave of sudden sleepiness
hit you. One of your eyes begins to sag, and then

02:54:29.902 --> 02:54:35.813
you (grunts) shake it off. Foam forming at the
corner of your mouth. The bard goes (yelling).

02:54:35.813 --> 02:54:37.896
ASHLY: I go (blows raspberry).

02:54:37.896 --> 02:54:46.999
MATT: Unaffected by it. That ends his turn. The
paladin, friend is gone, cannot do anything yet,

02:54:46.999 --> 02:54:53.014
is going to angrily move this way to begin a
pincer movement and is going to power attack you.

02:54:53.014 --> 02:54:55.187
That is a natural 20.

02:54:55.187 --> 02:54:56.692
ASHLY: Oh no!

02:54:56.692 --> 02:55:07.048
MATT: See if it confirms. With a natural 18, I'm
pretty sure that hits. That's times two on that.

02:55:07.048 --> 02:55:20.170
You take-- it's not too bad, you take 12 points of
damage as the sword streaks down, cleaving off

02:55:20.170 --> 02:55:26.555
part of your ear and ends up embedding in your
shoulder. You look over, grab the sword, and pull

02:55:26.555 --> 02:55:30.805
it out and throw her backward. She's caught off
guard by how this tiny thing has so much might.

02:55:30.805 --> 02:55:49.523
That ends the paladin's turn there. We're going to
bring us to the cleric. The cleric is going to see

02:55:49.523 --> 02:55:57.078
how rough this is, circumstantially. She is
looking over at the bombing one. Moves over here,

02:55:57.078 --> 02:56:03.695
turns to you and goes, "You will set nothing more
ablaze, creature!" I need you to make a will

02:56:03.695 --> 02:56:04.767
saving throw.

02:56:04.767 --> 02:56:11.229
MARISHA: Eh? What? Natural one. Again.

02:56:11.229 --> 02:56:13.781
IVAN: You shouldn't even sit next to me.

02:56:13.781 --> 02:56:16.493
PHIL: Your luck is rubbing off.

02:56:16.493 --> 02:56:25.973
MATT: As the Hold Person takes effect, your muscles
lock up. As you're reaching for a bomb (grunting).

02:56:25.973 --> 02:56:32.102
You just can't move! You see a grin across the
cleric's face. "That's what I thought." Ending the

02:56:32.102 --> 02:56:38.956
cleric's turn. The fighter is gone. Boom.
Grizznak, you're down to negative two.

02:56:38.956 --> 02:56:43.993
IVAN: Yeah, negative two. Can I make a
constitution check to see if I can stabilize?

02:56:43.993 --> 02:56:49.135
MATT: Go ahead and make a fortitude save.

02:56:49.135 --> 02:56:51.535
IVAN: Fortitude save. Oh! 20!

02:56:51.535 --> 02:56:56.112
MATT: 20? I'll say, for the sake of this, you
manage to stabilize, you're no longer bleeding.

02:56:56.112 --> 02:57:01.689
You're good. That ending your turn. Mezek, you're
up.

02:57:01.689 --> 02:57:07.360
TALIESIN: I'm going to run up to the cleric who
just paralyzed my friend. I'm going to run right

02:57:07.360 --> 02:57:11.165
up to him. Him, her, I don't actually know the
right pronouns for the cleric.

02:57:11.165 --> 02:57:17.411
MATT: You frog leap over the raging Piglet, and
land.

02:57:17.411 --> 02:57:25.822
TALIESIN: And I (yells) and I open palm into the
throat to use a stunning fist to try to silence her.

02:57:25.822 --> 02:57:27.506
MATT: Go for an attack.

02:57:27.506 --> 02:57:33.074
TALIESIN: That's a 15?

02:57:33.074 --> 02:57:35.588
MATT: 15 hits! She doesn't have a huge armor
class.

02:57:35.588 --> 02:57:50.687
TALIESIN: I said fist, I'm doing fist. That's five
points of damage and needs to make a fortitude save.

02:57:50.687 --> 02:57:54.121
MATT: Which she rolls a five, she does not.

02:57:54.121 --> 02:57:55.480
TALIESIN: She is stunned for a round.

02:57:55.480 --> 02:58:02.736
MATT: Yep. As you jump over, leap to the ground
and then shoryuken-like upper fist to her chin.

02:58:02.736 --> 02:58:10.189
You see a tooth go flying and her helmet gets set
off. She pulls back. She drops the holy symbol in

02:58:10.189 --> 02:58:15.471
her hand, which now hangs from a chain, grabs at
her head going (groaning) and is doubled over

02:58:15.471 --> 02:58:20.743
unable to gather her senses right now. Ending your
turn there. Browntooth, you're up.

02:58:20.743 --> 02:58:24.666
PHIL: Crossbow attack at the paladin.

02:58:24.666 --> 02:58:28.149
MATT: Paladin? All right, go for it. Roll the
attack for that one.

02:58:28.149 --> 02:58:34.568
ASHLY: It's 14.

02:58:34.568 --> 02:58:39.574
TALIESIN: You could try to maybe reroll it with a song.
You haven't used your song yet.

02:58:39.574 --> 02:58:41.718
MATT: You haven't used your song yet, if you
wanted.

02:58:41.718 --> 02:58:45.417
ASHLY: Maybe this'll be the first time that it
gets a better roll.

02:58:45.417 --> 02:58:53.539
PHIL: Yes, this is the one time. And my life's
not at stake. All right. I will sing my song.

02:58:53.539 --> 02:58:55.239
MATT: What's your song?

02:58:55.239 --> 02:59:02.635
PHIL: (sings) When Browntooth axe lifts up high, someone
is about to die! Someone will bleed, lots will get

02:59:02.635 --> 02:59:08.573
bit, though I'd rather avoid direct conflict. I'm
Browntooth the Rogue!

02:59:08.573 --> 02:59:15.156
MATT: Go ahead and reroll that as you steel
yourself, locking in another bolt into the

02:59:15.156 --> 02:59:16.189
crossbow.

02:59:16.189 --> 02:59:22.498
IVAN: Songs are cursed! All of our songs are
cursed!

02:59:22.498 --> 02:59:24.064
MATT: (singing) Goblin songs are cursed!

02:59:24.064 --> 02:59:25.765
MARISHA: People hate goblin songs.

02:59:25.765 --> 02:59:27.359
PHIL: It's worse than K-Pop.

02:59:27.359 --> 02:59:30.555
MATT: I got you a sad trombone for you, there.

02:59:30.555 --> 02:59:34.810
IVAN: Yep. Deserve it.

02:59:34.810 --> 02:59:38.054
PHIL: Man. At least I didn't die. No offense.

02:59:38.054 --> 02:59:39.931
IVAN: None taken.

02:59:39.931 --> 02:59:50.201
MATT: As the crossbow bolt goes off somewhere into
the skyline, you're realizing perhaps the distance

02:59:50.201 --> 02:59:54.466
game isn't working for you. Might need to get up
close and personal if you're going to land an

02:59:54.466 --> 02:59:56.523
attack here. Are you going to stay where you are?

02:59:56.523 --> 03:00:08.563
PHIL: Is the church that way?

03:00:08.563 --> 03:00:11.914
MATT: The church is up here. These are the steps
to the church.

03:00:11.914 --> 03:00:22.510
PHIL: I move over to the edge of the podium.

03:00:22.510 --> 03:00:24.367
MATT: Over here?

03:00:24.367 --> 03:00:25.457
PHIL: Yeah.

03:00:25.457 --> 03:00:28.471
MATT: Roll to see if you can remain stealthed.

03:00:28.471 --> 03:00:31.647
PHIL: 30.

03:00:31.647 --> 03:00:37.262
MATT: All right. Ending your turn. Brings it to
Snizzler. You're locked in place. Make a will

03:00:37.262 --> 03:00:41.604
saving throw to see if you can resist the effect
of the Hold Person spell.

03:00:41.604 --> 03:00:45.479
MARISHA: Just a straight will save?

03:00:45.479 --> 03:00:46.589
MATT: Yeah.

03:00:46.589 --> 03:00:47.888
MARISHA: Three.

03:00:47.888 --> 03:00:50.542
TALIESIN: How is that even humanly--?

03:00:50.542 --> 03:00:54.547
MATT: Unable to shake the effect. You're still
locked in place. Hand on the bomb. You're looking

03:00:54.547 --> 03:00:58.215
down at it. You were about to light it and your
hand is hovering there and you're like

03:00:58.215 --> 03:00:59.423
(strains).

03:00:59.423 --> 03:01:03.664
TALIESIN: I cast Methadone.

03:01:03.664 --> 03:01:05.461
MATT: Piglet, you're up.

03:01:05.461 --> 03:01:10.551
ASHLY: I'm going to rage. I'm going to attack the
paladin.

03:01:10.551 --> 03:01:13.119
MATT: You can both hammer and bite.

03:01:13.119 --> 03:01:15.044
ASHLY: I'm going to do both.

03:01:15.044 --> 03:01:16.528
MATT: Go for it.

03:01:16.528 --> 03:01:18.378
ASHLY: 18 plus nine.

03:01:18.378 --> 03:01:20.464
MATT: That hits. Go ahead and roll the hammer
damage.

03:01:20.464 --> 03:01:23.117
MARISHA: Roll that hammer damage!

03:01:23.117 --> 03:01:25.017
ASHLY: That is 12.

03:01:25.017 --> 03:01:31.177
MATT: 12? Ooh! As you bring up and slam the hammer
down, she pushes the shield up to block the blow,

03:01:31.177 --> 03:01:35.968
but the mallet catches over the top. The sheer
weight of it pushes the shield away as it comes

03:01:35.968 --> 03:01:41.636
down and slams into the side of her chin. You can
see the jaw breaks from the impact. A little bit

03:01:41.636 --> 03:01:46.203
of blood begins to trickle out of the corner of her
mouth. She's like (pained grunting). She spits a

03:01:46.203 --> 03:01:48.938
glob of blood across her otherwise pristine silver
armor.

03:01:48.938 --> 03:01:51.801
PHIL: Seriously, she's all about cliches. Does she
do this?

03:01:51.801 --> 03:01:55.620
MATT: Roll for the bite attack.

03:01:55.620 --> 03:02:01.044
ASHLY: 18 plus four.

03:02:01.044 --> 03:02:04.659
MATT: That also hits. Go ahead and roll damage.

03:02:04.659 --> 03:02:06.199
ASHLY: A d3 plus three.

03:02:06.199 --> 03:02:08.636
MATT: Roll a d6, halve that, add three.

03:02:08.636 --> 03:02:11.709
ASHLY: Four.

03:02:11.709 --> 03:02:15.265
MATT: Four points of damage. As she's reacting
from that and spits the blood out, looks down, you

03:02:15.265 --> 03:02:19.960
run up the side of her shield and bite into the
chin you just broke and tear a chunk out of her

03:02:19.960 --> 03:02:26.041
face! She's like, (screaming) "Who does
that?!"

03:02:26.041 --> 03:02:28.717
ASHLY: Piglet does, bitches!

03:02:28.717 --> 03:02:36.073
MATT: That ends Piglet's turn. The bard, whose
spell has been less than active, and the wizard who

03:02:36.073 --> 03:02:41.667
spent his last term in absolute horror of his
friend, regains his senses and is going to step up.

03:02:41.667 --> 03:02:43.495
ASHLY: Oh, I forgot about the wizard.

03:02:43.495 --> 03:02:47.511
MATT: Yeah, the wizard hid off to the side and
watched his friend get beheaded and spent the turn

03:02:47.511 --> 03:02:55.495
looking in horror. The bard is going to attempt to
cast Sleep on you again.

03:02:55.495 --> 03:02:57.992
Make another willpower save.

03:02:57.992 --> 03:03:03.905
ASHLY: I'm raging, so it still applies, right? 18
plus three.

03:03:03.905 --> 03:03:08.763
MATT: 18 plus three. Once again, shrug off the
effect. And he's like, "Why won't you stay down,

03:03:08.763 --> 03:03:13.215
"stupid thing?!" He's pointing his finger,
clutching his flute angrily in the other hand.

03:03:13.215 --> 03:03:15.215
Nothing is affecting you.

03:03:15.215 --> 03:03:16.483
TALIESIN: Red Bull!

03:03:16.483 --> 03:03:23.324
MATT: He's going to rush over to the side behind
the cleric now and be like, "Can you heal me?

03:03:23.324 --> 03:03:30.688
"Please!" He's running off to the side and asking
for a heal. The paladin is going to, as a reaction

03:03:30.688 --> 03:03:39.955
to you, furiously swing at you with the longsword.
That is a 22 to hit.

03:03:39.955 --> 03:03:41.675
ASHLY: It hits.

03:03:41.675 --> 03:03:48.697
MATT: That hits. You take seven points of slashing
damage as the blade streaks down across you.

03:03:48.697 --> 03:03:54.631
You're still chewing the chunk of her face that's
running around in your jaw, but the blade goes

03:03:54.631 --> 03:04:00.145
across the front of your torso, and leaves an
opening that begins to spill dark, brackish,

03:04:00.145 --> 03:04:05.351
goblin blood. You don't even feel the pain. You're
in such a furious bloodlust right now.

03:04:05.351 --> 03:04:08.075
ASHLY: So, next round might be my last round,
guys.

03:04:08.075 --> 03:04:11.119
PHIL: When we get down to two, I'm going to take
off.

03:04:11.119 --> 03:04:13.633
ASHLY: I got 11 hit points left.

03:04:13.633 --> 03:04:15.327
MATT: The wizard's going to step forward now.

03:04:15.327 --> 03:04:17.633
TALIESIN: This round might be your last round.

03:04:17.633 --> 03:04:22.728
MATT: Going to go ahead and cast Magic Missile.
One arcs off at you while you're held in place.

03:04:22.728 --> 03:04:24.431
MARISHA: Oh, shit!

03:04:24.431 --> 03:04:30.047
MATT: One's going to streak off and hit you.
Mezek, you take two points of force damage.

03:04:30.047 --> 03:04:37.787
Snizzler, you take three points of force damage as
two missiles arc off and slam into the sides of

03:04:37.787 --> 03:04:46.451
you from the arcane nature of the spell. That ends
his turn. The cleric can't do anything, is stunned

03:04:46.451 --> 03:04:51.812
this round. Manages to shrug it off, but has
absolutely no way of using any of her abilities

03:04:51.812 --> 03:04:56.369
because of the fist in the face she got from
Mezek. Grizznak!

03:04:56.369 --> 03:04:59.145
IVAN: (singing) I found a nest of baby birds.

03:04:59.145 --> 03:05:03.188
MATT: Finishing that. Mezek, it's your turn.

03:05:03.188 --> 03:05:13.811
TALIESIN: I'm going to use my Flurry of Blows, with my
quarterstaff, and I'm going to use Stunning Fist, again.

03:05:13.811 --> 03:05:15.151
MATT: Your last?

03:05:15.151 --> 03:05:16.159
TALIESIN: Yeah.

03:05:16.159 --> 03:05:19.011
MATT: Go for it! So you are doing two punches or
two hits with your quarterstaff?

03:05:19.011 --> 03:05:21.299
TALIESIN: Well, Stunning First, is it fist or
first?

03:05:21.299 --> 03:05:26.439
MATT: Stunning Fist is as an attack; you can have
it be a Stunning Fist attack.

03:05:26.439 --> 03:05:31.078
TALIESIN: So I'm going to (punching sounds). I'm
going to use the quarterstaff.

03:05:31.078 --> 03:05:33.136
MATT: So roll for that, see if it hits.

03:05:33.136 --> 03:05:39.255
TALIESIN: For the Stunning Fist first; that's 20.

03:05:39.255 --> 03:05:46.177
MATT: 20, that hits. Go ahead and roll damage on
that. Rolls a seven.

03:05:46.177 --> 03:05:48.083
TALIESIN: That's six points of damage.

03:05:48.083 --> 03:05:51.794
MATT: Six points of damage and she is stunned
again. Quarterstaff clocks her upside the head,

03:05:51.794 --> 03:05:55.547
now causing the armor to bend in on her temple and
one eye has gone a little

03:05:55.547 --> 03:05:57.456
cross-eyed from the impact.

03:05:57.456 --> 03:05:58.848
TALIESIN: So I'm going to hit her again.

03:05:58.848 --> 03:06:00.031
PHIL: Who'd you hit?

03:06:00.031 --> 03:06:03.581
TALIESIN: The cleric. The cleric is unconscious.
They can't do another round of anything.

03:06:03.581 --> 03:06:04.770
ASHLY: That's true.

03:06:04.770 --> 03:06:05.895
TALIESIN: Hitting her again.

03:06:05.895 --> 03:06:07.171
MATT: Go for it.

03:06:07.171 --> 03:06:09.105
TALIESIN: That's 12.

03:06:09.105 --> 03:06:11.765
MATT: 12 total bonus?

03:06:11.765 --> 03:06:13.039
TALIESIN: To hit.

03:06:13.039 --> 03:06:18.192
MATT: She is currently flat-footed with the armor
that's still 14, so yeah.

03:06:18.192 --> 03:06:20.432
ASHLY: Is it time?

03:06:20.432 --> 03:06:21.574
TALIESIN: It's time.

03:06:21.574 --> 03:06:27.470
Reroll that. (singing) Mezek, Mezek the
